review_text: After all the hype I heard from my friends about this place, finally I got to try on my recent visit to Yogya. First, I really was surprised with the pricing for all the food presented on the menu, despite hearing those claims already from my friends. There is no where else that I know of that has prices as affordable! Carpaccio, Escargot, Steak, Pasta. These all could be found in the range of 50k - 150k.  Insane! I was really happy with the authenticity of the establishment as well. We came as a group as we ordered a whole bunch of food. The menu was really alluring. When the food came, it was really HUGE PORTION. Most of the menu, the group really enjoyed them. We ordered the soup, pizza, the steak, the appetizer tuna, king prawn special of the day, Seafood pasta, the Duck with potato gratin. Personally, the food were just mostly okay for me. It didnt quite leave any lasting impression for a revisit. Some menu were too salty (potato gratin, king prawn), and the juices were way too diluted. The one that tasted better is probably the Duck. My least favorite is probably the Seafood pasta, it has some artificial taste somehow. My other guess is probably the kitchen was really busy, because its almost full house when we got there, could probably be reason the food isnt as good as the hype for me.

The food is really good here, highly recommended if youre a little homesick for Europe. Unfortunately the service is a bit slow, but it works in principle and is very friendly. Would go there again. The pizza calzone was a monster.
review_translated_text: Das Essen ist richtig gut hier, warmtens zu empfehlen wenn man etwas Heimweh nach Europa hat. Leider ist das Service etwas zah, funktioniert aber prinzipiell und ist sehr freundlich. Wurde wieder dorthin gehen. Die Pizza Calzone war ein Monster.

review_text: Meskipun sempet waiting list tp saya & suami sependapat kalo mediterrania ini worth it. Kami order feta & olives, mediterrania pizza, escargot, & piece of beef pan roasted. Buat kami semuanya cocok di lidah kami (tp untuk feta & olives nya agak repot karena olives nya masih the whole fruit bukan potongan ). All in cuma 500k include minumannya (buat kami ini ngga mahal untuk ukuran resto turis jogja). Kenyang dan puas bgt. Warm hospitality juga, pelayanannya cepet untuk makanan tipe kayak gini walau resto rame. Dan waitress nya sangat baik dalam menjelaskan menu2 nya. Anw, resto ini bukan tipe yg cocok kalau mau intimate dinner menurutku sih, karena space antar meja nya yg begitu deket. Space parkir nya jg terbatas (typical resto di prawirotaman)
review_translated_text: Even though there was a waiting list, my husband & I agreed that the Mediterranean was worth it. We ordered feta & olives, Mediterranean pizza, escargot, & a piece of pan roasted beef. For us, everything suits our taste buds (but for the feta & olives its a bit tricky because the olives are still the whole fruit, not pieces ). All in only 500k including drinks (for us this is not expensive for a Jogja tourist restaurant). Very full and satisfied. Warm hospitality too, fast service for this type of food even though the restaurant is busy. And the waitress was very good at explaining the menu. Anw, this restaurant is not the type that is suitable if you want an intimate dinner, in my opinion, because the space between the tables is so close. Parking space is also limited (typical restaurant in Prawirotaman)

Tidak seperti yang mahal tapi tidak ada lauknya  eskrim, makanannya enak. Cuma kemaren pesen lemon tea kalo ga salah, malah coca cola dikasihnya  tapi tak apa apa sih
review_translated_text: When I come here I forget what date it is, usually I just buy mcflurry ice cream   in my opinion... its better to buy it here if you eat in Malioboro   if mcd is delicious the food is delicious. Not like the expensive ones but there are no side dishes  ice cream, the food is delicious. Just yesterday I ordered lemon tea if Im not mistaken, he gave me Coca Cola instead  but its okay

review_text: Menikmati makan siang di Malioboro tapi di luar benar-benar panas, jadi ya paling sejuk makan di McD Malioboro Mall. Secara, si kecil juga suka banget dengan fried chicken dan si besar paling suka dengan es krim jadi ya sudah pas lah kalau kita makan disini. Sebetulnya saya dan istri kepingin banget kulineran ke beberapa tempat yang sudah kami hunting tapi karena anak-anak sudah tidak sabar jadi disini tempat terbaik bagi anak-anakku.
review_translated_text: Enjoying lunch at Malioboro but its really hot outside, so its coolest to eat at McD Malioboro Mall. In fact, the little one also really likes fried chicken and the big one really likes ice cream so its only fitting that we eat here. Actually, my wife and I really wanted to go to some of the places we had hunted for culinary delights, but because the kids couldnt wait, this was the best place for my kids.

review_text: Sama kayak mcd pada umumnya, karna di mall jadi tempat duduknya terbatas & kalo rame bisa ga dpt tempat duduk,, antrinya juga pjg apalagi pas weekend & Libur sekolah, mudah di cari ketika masuk mall.
review_translated_text: Just like McDs in general, because in malls there are limited seats & if its busy you might not get a seat, the queue is also long, especially on weekends & school holidays, its easy to find when entering the mall.

review_text: Kayaknya cukup terakhir ini saya beli makan dicabang plaza malioboro. Yg tempo hari dpt ayam yg kyak minyaknya sdh brkli2 bt goreng, ayamnya bnr2 tampilannya gak bgt berminyak kecoklatan kyak jlantah pd nempel ,sama olive enakan olive khusus cabang yg malioboro. Dan yg kmrn kentangnya asiiinnn banget Kl kesini kyky cukup beli eskrim aja, kl pgn mkn berat lebih baik yg cabang sudirman atau ambarukmo
review_translated_text: I think this is the last time I bought food at the Malioboro Plaza branch. The other day I got chicken that looked like the oil had just been fried, the chicken really didnt look like it was oily, brownish like it was stuck to it, the olive was delicious, especially the Malioboro branch. And yesterday the potatoes were really delicious If you come here, just buy ice cream, if you want to eat a heavy meal, its better to go to the Sudirman or Ambarukmo branches.

review_text: Three times we visited McDonalds Jogja. We got Cold burgers and french fries 3 times . We had asked for extra toppings on our burgers and were charged more $$ and got nothing extra.  This store is not a very good standard for McDonalds in Indonesia or the world. Very disappointed. The toilets smells of urine . The manager needs to fix this as soon as possible. Come on McDonalds look after your customers please . Please take care, sorry for the bad review. Looking at the other reviews we are not the only people dissatisfied.

review_translated_text: The location is in the middle of a residential area, closes around 23.00. There is a smoking area, the toilets are clean. review_text: Tempat untuk duduk sejenak ketika di jogja, bisa baca buku , ada mushola nya, pelayanan ramah, untuk harga rata rata 30an per menu, ada 2 lantai , indoor dan outdoor, sepertinya bakal kesini lagi kalau pas ke jogja dan mau cari tempat buat baca buku
review_translated_text: A place to sit for a while when in Jogja, you can read a book, there is a prayer room, friendly service, for an average price of 30 per menu, there are 2 floors, indoor and outdoor, looks like I will come here again if I go to Jogja and want to find a place to read a book

review_text: Lokasinya deket Tugu Jogja. Cafenya enak buat nugas, kerja, atau sekedar ngobrol-ngobrol. Pelayanannya sangat baik, ramah, dan mau menjelaskan dengan sabar. Tempatnya ada 2 lantai dan ada indoor maupun outdoor. Untuk rasa minumannya enak, kombuchanya seger, sedangkan americanonya bikin melek lama. Untuk harganya standar cafe. Ada banyak buku yang bisa dibaca ditempat. Kemudian ada musholanya juga di lantai 2. Parking: Parkirnya dipinggir jalan, untuk motor bayar 2.000. Ada tukang parkirnya yang sangat membantu.
review_translated_text: The location is near the Jogja Monument. The cafe is good for doing assignments, working or just chatting. The service is very good, friendly, and willing to explain patiently. The place has 2 floors and is indoor and outdoor. The taste of the drink is delicious, the kombucha is fresh, while the americano keeps you awake for a long time. For cafe standard prices. There are many books that can be read on site. Then there is also a prayer room on the 2nd floor. Parking: Parking is on the side of the road, for motorbikes you pay 2,000. There is a parking attendant who is very helpful.

review_text: We found this place while on the hunt for a place to eat and have a drink on a Friday evening (during ramadan - so many places werent serving alcohol). What a hidden gem it was! The location is a bit off Malioboro and rather quiet, so we were sceptical while walking there, but once we saw it, we were pleasantly surprised. It has a really chill ambiance. The food was good and we were happy to find out that they actually have a wine list -  a rarity in Indonesia in our experience. Its just a couple of options, but better than nothing! We went for a Sauvignon Blanc from Bali, but there were some international options as well. The best surprise was the live music though! While we were eating a band arrived and they were actually great. All in all, an excellent evening!

review_text: Rekomendasi resto yang homey. Tempatnya minimalis tapi artistik. Sudut-sudut ruangan banyak banget spot yg Instagramable. Ada indoor sama semi outdoor areanya. Agak pricey tapi oke, nggk mengecewakan. Makanannya enak, specially the chicken burger. Aku prefer chicken burger daripada beef burgernya. Racikan sausnya enak, nampol banget. Minumannya juga oke. Service nya juga ramah, komunikatif, dan humoris. Toilet bersih. Cashless available. Ada kang parkir yg bantu rapikan kendaraan.
review_translated_text: Homey restaurant recommendation. The place is minimalist but artistic. There are lots of Instagrammable spots in the corners of the room. There are indoor and semi outdoor areas. A bit pricey but okay, didnt disappoint. The food is delicious, especially the chicken burger. I prefer the chicken burger over the beef burger. The sauce mixture is delicious, really delicious. The drinks are okay too. The service is also friendly, communicative and humorous. Clean toilets. Cashless available. There is a parking attendant who helps tidy up the vehicle.

review_text: Dari awal berdiri 2017 zamannya cuma jual cake sampai skr sudah full jual F&B,gk pernah absen tiap kali ke jogja selain makanan nya enak,suasanan homiiee dan gk kalah pelayanan nya sangat ramah dan jogja banget,Namanya Mas didit yg siap melayani dengam tulus sepenuh hati,tiap ke tempat ini mas didit selalu memberikan ruang kepuasaan pelayanan tersendiri di samping enaknya makanan dan minuman. Terimakasih mas didit.
review_translated_text: Since its inception in 2017, it was just selling cakes until now it is full of selling F&B, I have never been absent every time I have been to Jogja, apart from the food being delicious, the atmosphere is homie and not to mention the service is very friendly and really Jogja, his name is Mas Didit who is ready to serve with all his heart and sincerity Every time you go to this place, Mas Didit always provides a room of satisfaction with his own service in addition to delicious food and drinks. Thank you bro Didit.

review_text: Review ditulis di hari yang sama saat kunjungan. Ini pengalaman pertama kali datang ke sini. Kesan pertama : tempatnya adem banget. Terbilang nyaman, dingin ACnya, dan ada area outdoor juga. 5/5 untuk kenyamanan tempatnya. Semua menu makanan kosong (spaghetti/nasi/kentang) hanya tersedia bleger beef (blegger chicken kosong) dan minuman. Paling berkesan sama kopi koplo bia. Penilaian untuk kopi 5/5 enak banget, creamynya berasa padahal esnya udah mencair, dan single shot espressonya pas buat yang pengen ngopi ngopi ringan. Kalo pengen double shot, bisa pilih kopi koplo abi ya. Penilaian untuk blegernya 4/5 Suka sama saos mayonya, seperti racikan khusus karena cenderung manis. Tingkat serat dagingnya dan roti bun nya oke. Penilaian untuk pelayanan 3.5/5 Maaf untuk penilaian kasir kurang memuaskan sebab kasir beralasan uang pengunjung besar semua (diminta bayar pakai uang pas aja atau qris). Semoga ke depannya bisa lebih diatur lagi uang kecil yang tersedia di kasir. Untuk waiternya sangat ramah senyum. Nilai plus. Sehat sehat berkah selalu mas waiter. Aamiin. Fasilitas lainnya 4/5 Tersedia musholla dengan area yang cukupan, area indoor dan outdoor, dan toilet. Area parkir terbilang cukup terbatas. Toilet perempuan kurang pas untuk dikunci. Semoga segera diperbaiki demi keamanan dan kenyamanan customer. Untuk yang penasaran sama restonya kak Zaskia A Mecca, monggo mampir pinarak.
review_translated_text: Review written on the same day of visit. This is my first experience coming here. First impression: the place is really cool. It is said to be comfortable, the AC is cold, and there is an outdoor area too. 5/5 for the comfort of the place. All food menus are empty (spaghetti/rice/potatoes) only bleger beef (empty blegger chicken) and drinks are available. Most impressive is Koplo Bia coffee. Rating for coffee 5/5 Its really delicious, it feels creamy even though the ice has melted, and the single shot of espresso is perfect for those who want a light drink of coffee. If you want a double shot, you can choose Koplo Abi coffee. The rating for the blender is 4/5 I like the mayo sauce, its like a special concoction because it tends to be sweet. The fiber level of the meat and bread is okay. Rating for service 3.5/5 Sorry for the cashiers assessment which was less than satisfactory because the cashier argued that all the visitors money was large (they were asked to pay using just the right money or qris). Hopefully in the future we can better regulate the small money available at the cashier. The waiter is very friendly with a smile. Plus value. Always healthy, blessed, sir, waiter. Amen. Other facilities 4/5 There is a prayer room with sufficient area, indoor and outdoor areas, and toilets. The parking area is quite limited. The womens toilet is not suitable for locking. Hopefully it will be repaired soon for customer safety and comfort. For those who are curious about Sis Zaskia A Meccas restaurant, please stop by Pinarak.

review_text: Ke Mamahke untuk beli cake reguler double chocolate nya karena direcommend teman. Untuk tempatnya nyaman banget dan staff nya ramah banget, sabar ngejelasinnya. Untuk kue nya sendiri uniknya di tengah2 ada lapisan pastry gitu, dan cokelatnya tidak terlalu manis. Sayangnya pas saya datang yang ukuran reguler hanya tersedia yang double chocolate, redvelvet dan tiramisu. Tiramisu pun tinggal 1 dan keburu dibeli teman saya. Nextnya mau coba untuk yang keju karena secara pribadi saya lebih suka keju dripada cokelat.
review_translated_text: Went to Mamahke to buy the regular double chocolate cake because it was recommended by a friend. The place is very comfortable and the staff is very friendly, patient in explaining things. The unique thing about the cake itself is that there is a layer of pastry in the middle, and the chocolate is not too sweet. Unfortunately, when I arrived, the regular size was only available in double chocolate, redvelvet and tiramisu. There was only 1 Tiramisu left and my friend bought it in a hurry. Next, I want to try the cheese one because personally I prefer cheese over chocolate.

review_text: Makanannya enak, tempatnya juga nyaman, parkir juga luas. Yang perlu diperbaiki adalah metode pembayaran, Restoran tidak menerima pembayaran QRIS, untuk debit kartu yang digunakan terbatas hanya BRI dan Mandiri. Metode transfer bisa dilakukan tapi harus menunggu konfirmasi dari pemilik dulu apakah uangnya sudah masuk atau belum. Jadi secara tidak langsung harus menyiapkan uang tunai. Cukup disayangkan.

What needs to be improved is the payment method, the restaurant does not accept QRIS payments, the debit cards used are limited to only BRI and Mandiri. The transfer method can be done but you have to wait for confirmation from the owner first whether the money has been received or not. So indirectly you have to prepare cash. Quite unfortunate.

review_text: Hot Chocolate enak, cuma agak terlalu manis untuk preferensiku. Hot Chocolate yang 77% ini kental banget, jauh lebih kental dari yang 69% diikuti 86%. Nyobain juga Fluffy Pancake+Gelato nya, rasanya oke lah, kemarin dapetnya dingin mungkin memang udah ready ya dan di simpan di kulkas. Tempatnya bersih dan nyaman, bisa beli oleh-oleh juga untuk yang suka cokelat, untuk 80g harganya di 40rb-60rb, lumayan mahal sih. Kalau ke sini aku recommend Hot/Iced Chocolate.
review_translated_text: The Hot Chocolate was delicious, just a little too sweet for my preference. The 77% Hot Chocolate is really thick, much thicker than the 69% followed by 86%. Also try the Fluffy Pancake + Gelato, it tastes okay, yesterday I got it cold, maybe it was already ready and stored it in the refrigerator. The place is clean and comfortable, you can also buy souvenirs for those who like chocolate, for 80g the price is around 40 thousand-60 thousand, quite expensive. If you come here, I recommend Hot/Iced Chocolate.

Gelatonya juga enak. Saya pesan Strawberry Cheesecake; rasa strawberry & cheesecakenya itu berasa, nendang, pas pokoknya. Terus teksturnya lembut & gak cepet leleh. Tempat yamg wajib dikunjungi! Recommended!

Original review pre vomit: The 77% hot chocolate is perfect: creamy, tasty, hint of sweetness The 86% was a bit too bitter for me and not creamy enough, it was somehow more watery. The fluffy pancakes were really good, very fluffy, very nice and delicate taste, and you can choose the ice cream flavour you want on top. Vegetarian options: The non-sweet dishes have no vegetarian option.

Despite the hot 77% dark chocolate and the fluffy pancake tasting very good, both my partner and I felt sick afterwards and had to throw up. Were not sure what the cause was (bad milk/ ice cream/ pancake or the little chocolates to try) but we obviously didnt enjoy the aftereffects of our breakfast. It looks cozy and the personnel is very nice, speaking English very well.
As far as stopping here, the taste of food, drinks, gelato and snacks... Everything is satisfactory..

review_text: I googled the best coffee shop in the city and Tamamera among the top 5. So I went here after dinner with my friend. Very polite & professional barista. I love the dim light environment at outside sitting area. Generally all sitting area a bit rigid coz by furniture design-but I dont mind as my priority is the coffee. The coffee- I ordered hot latte, then flat white: professionally prepared with excellent taste- niche quality for me. I came again the next day after lunch hour before traveling back to Kuala Lumpur. And always 2 cups when I love the coffee quality. Will go here again if I visit Jogja.

review_text: Tempat ini punya dua pilihan tempat, outdoor dan indoor. Tempatnya cukup luas dan berada cukup strategis di dekat tugu jogja. Nyobain cold brew white, kopo dan susu tapi rasanya dominan susu. Pancakenya biasa aja, tidak ada yang spesial. Penyajiannya juga cukup lama. Sebaiknya kalau lapar sangat jangn kesini. Disini buat slow-slow saja, ngobrol2 santai, kerja juga ok karena relatif tidak terlalu ramai. Disini tersedia toilet dan mushola juga, jadi jika berlama-lama disini aman. Bagusnya disini semua minuman dan makanan yang dimakan ditempat disajikan pakai wadah yang tidak sekali pakai jadi lebih ramah lingkungan. Sedotan tulisannya pakai yang bisa terurai. Mungkin baiknya pakai stainless saja supaya tidak ada sampah.
review_translated_text: This place has two choices of places, outdoor and indoor. The place is quite spacious and is quite strategic near the Jogja monument. Tried cold brew white, kopo and milk but the taste was dominant with milk. The pancakes are just ordinary, nothing special. The presentation also took quite a long time. If youre really hungry, dont come here. Here, just take it slow, chat casually, work is also ok because its relatively not too busy. There are toilets and prayer rooms here too, so if you linger here its safe. The good thing here is that all drinks and food eaten at the place are served in non-single-use containers so they are more environmentally friendly. Use biodegradable writing straws. Maybe its better to just use stainless so theres no waste.

Ketemu temen disini. Suasana di dalam Tanamera asik buat ngobrol santai berlama-lama, atau untuk fokus bekerja. Tidak terlalu ramai waktu datang kesini, dan langsung pesan menu yang diinginkan. Selain kopi, ada tea, dan menu makanannya pun cukup beragam dari snack sampai makan beratnya. Pesan langsung bayar. Makanan dan minuman datang tidak terlalu lama. Untuk harga, standard coffeeshop 25-40 ribuan. Rasa makanan, perlu diberi masukan untuk rasa makanan yang buat saya sangat kurang oke. Pisang goreng sebenernya enak, saya kurang tau apakah standardnya pisang goreng disini memang gurih tepungnya? Karena pisangnya sendiri tidak manis, dengan taburan gula halus juga tidak menambah rasa manisnya. Lalu potato wedges, tidak gurih, hanya penuh bubuk paprika. Ada juga yang saya pesan chicken salted egg, salted egg-nya jauh dari harapan. Kurang tasty, chicken plain. Hanya parkiran terasa sangat panas disana karena tidak ada atap pelindung kendaraan. Parkir tidak berbayar.
review_translated_text: Meet friends here. The atmosphere inside Tanamera is great for chatting casually for a long time, or for focusing on work. Its not too busy when you come here, and immediately order the menu you want. Apart from coffee, there is tea, and the food menu is quite varied, from snacks to heavy meals. Order and pay immediately. Food and drinks didnt take too long to come. For prices, standard coffeeshops are 25-40 thousand. The taste of the food, needs to be given input for the taste of the food which for me is not very good. The fried bananas are actually delicious, I dont know if the standard for fried bananas here is that they are really tasty? Because the banana itself is not sweet, sprinkling it with powdered sugar doesnt add to the sweet taste. Then potato wedges, not tasty, just full of paprika powder. I also ordered chicken salted eggs, the salted eggs were far from expectations. Not tasty, plain chicken. Only the parking lot felt very hot there because there was no roof to protect the vehicle. Parking is unpaid.

review_text: Suka disini, buat saya TANAMERA salah satu tempat yg memiliki good service in jogjakarta, ramah supel,, sebagai customer saya netasa nyaman. Makanannya enak, ngga asin dan no msg. Coffe nya TOPbgt, arabica, creamy, afa taste sweet nya padal no sugar

review_text: Makanan di tempat ini Lezat dan selalu lebih baik kualitasnya. Setiap kali saya Datang, Makanannya Terasa lebih baik. Ayamnya keras, Tapi Tetap Terasa gurih dan tidak berminyak. seafood disini jauh lebih segar dibanding ayam atau bebeknya. Tersedia minuman hangat atau dingin disini, semuannya disajikan dengan baik. Layanan reservasi sangat mudah dipesan, Dan tanpa reservasi pun, tetap dapat tempat yang strategis. Pelayan yang ramah disini Membuat restoran ini lebih baik. Tempat disini memiliki pemandangan yang indah, tapi kualitas pendopo dan kolam disini dibawah rata rata. Memiliki suasana yang standar dan meja yang rendah, tempat ini bahkan memiliki beberapa foto dari tahun 2011-2016, sedangkan restorannya beru berdiri pada tahun 2020. Keluarga saya sudah 3 kali datang kesini, dan tidak pernah kecewa dengan restoran ini. Tapi selalu ada ruang untuk Perbaikan dan Improvisasi, Mengingat kekurangan tempat ini.
review_translated_text: The food at this place is Delicious and always better quality. Every time I come, the food tastes better. The chicken is tough, but still tastes delicious and not oily. The seafood here is much fresher than the chicken or duck. Hot or cold drinks are available here, all served well. The reservation service is very easy to order, and even without a reservation, you can still get a strategic place. The friendly waiters here make this restaurant better. The place here has beautiful views, but the quality of the pavilion and pool here is below average. Having a standard atmosphere and low tables, this place even has some photos from 2011-2016, while the restaurant was only founded in 2020. My family has come here 3 times, and has never been disappointed with this restaurant. But there is always room for Improvement and Improvisation, Considering the shortcomings of this place.

review_translated_text: Ive been here several times and tried several menus. In terms of food and drink, the chicken burger is satisfying both in terms of size, taste and visuals, for the drinks its a bit less so, the visuals are really interesting but the taste is hmmm, dry in my personal opinion, no hate. My favorite is the chicken burger which is awesome, drink it because according to my taste I keep ordering mineral water, French fries + tartar sauce, and the mac n cheese is okay but not impressive and its better to eat it when its hot. In terms of place and atmosphere, I really like the concept, lots of old school and cute ornaments, they also provide reading books, its just a shame that the 2nd floor is stiflingly hot, its true that the 2nd floor doesnt have air conditioning, but the stifling heat is not because theres no air conditioning, but Why, I dont know even though the doors and windows are wide open but the air is bitter. Here the concept is self-service, so when youve finished eating, its cleaned up, theres also a place to put the tray near the stairs.

review_text: Untuk rasa burgernya si enak. Sakuragi dan megumi sih yang aku suka. Tapi untuk mac n cheese sorry rasanya terlalu enek di aku, mungkin rasanya kureng atau emang gak cocok di lidah aku. Untuk harga burger lumayan si, cuma karna rasanya enak jadi ya worth it lah. Lumayan bikin kenyang. Beda orang, beda pendapat tapi menurut aku harga minumannya mahal dan temen temenku jg tidak direkomendasikan karena rasanya kurang, jadi aku pesen air mineral. Semoga jadi masukan ya karena udah beberapa orang yg bilang. Tempatnya aesthetic walau sempit. Waktu itu aku traktiran bawa beberapa temen (berenam) dan untungnya dapet tempat yg agak luas di lantai 1. Bersih kok, cuma waktu itu toiletnya bau pol. Konsepnya disini self service. Untuk pelayanan (kasir) kalau berdasarkan penilaian, beberapa bilang jutek. Jujur keliatan dr mimiknya si iya , tapi aslinya ya biasa aj sih mungkin ekspresinya aja yg bgitu cuma emg temenku beberapa bilang sering dapet yang jutek jadi ini juga ditraining lagi aja. Tapi untung aku dapet kasir yang ramah, friendly, dan profesional   . Waktu itu minta bolpoin ke salah satu mbak nya (beda orang) buat nulis di dinding juga dia lebih ramah lagi dan juga bantu nyariin. Baik sekali, terima kasih ya. Next time aku pengen nulis di kertas yg di dinding itu. Lalu selain tentang toilet, mau saran juga untuk disediakan tisu di setiap meja karena burgernya tu besar kan, mana bersaus juga pasti makannya agak berantakan entah sausnya tumpah atau jatuh. Jadi gak perlu bolak balik ambil tisu. Ini aku saran gini soalnya waktu aku kesana tisu masih di satu tempat. Bukan mager, cuma bolak balik jg agak malu dan bikin org risih juga. Overall aku puas sih. Aku udah suruh temen temenku dateng kesini dan udah banyak dari mereka yang kesini . Soon aku mau traktiran sama temen temenku lagi yang lain disini juga. Dan juga mau nyoba ngedate disini juga. Semoga beberapa masukan sudah diterima dan dijalankan. Sukses terus. Pengen tau apakah disini bisa reservasi atau enggak ya untuk +-10 orang? Makasih.
review_translated_text: The taste of the burger is delicious. I like Sakuragi and Megumi. But for mac n cheese, sorry, it tastes too good for me, maybe it tastes dry or just doesnt suit my taste buds. For the price of the burger its not bad, just because it tastes good its worth it. Its quite filling. Different people, different opinions, but in my opinion the price of the drink is expensive and my friends didnt recommend it because it doesnt taste enough, so I ordered mineral water. Hopefully this will be input, because several people have already said so. The place is aesthetic even though it is narrow. At that time I brought a few friends (six) as a treat and luckily I got a fairly spacious place on the 1st floor. It was clean, only at that time the toilet smelled bad. The concept here is self service. Regarding the service (cashier), based on the assessment, some said it was rude. Honestly, it looks like that from his expression, yes, but in reality its just normal, maybe its just his expression thats like that, its just that some of my friends say they often get dirty guys, so this is just training again. But luckily I got a cashier who was friendly, welcoming and professional   . At that time, I asked one of the ladies (a different person) for a pen to write on the wall, she was even friendlier and also helped me look for it. Very good, thank you. Next time I want to write on the paper on the wall. Then apart from the toilets, I would also like to suggest that there be tissues provided at every table because the burgers are big, right? If you eat them with sauce, its bound to be a bit messy to eat, whether the sauce spills or falls. So you dont need to go back and forth to get tissue. I suggest this because when I went there the tissue was still in one place. Its not mager, its just that going back and forth is a bit embarrassing and makes people uncomfortable too. Overall Im satisfied. Ive told my friends to come here and many of them have already come here . Soon I want to treat my other friends here too. And also want to try dating here too. Hopefully some of the input has been received and implemented. Continued success. Want to know whether you can make reservations here or not for +-10 people? Thanks.

review_text: Parkir : sama dengan parkir pantai indrayanti, luas dan cukup banyak muat mobil. 4 of 5. Lokasi  dan atmosfer : pas di bibir pantai indrayanti jadi bisa mwnikmati angin pantai dan viem nya sambil makan. 5 of 5. Makanan : pesan cumi goreng telur asin. Enak, but not the best one lah. porsi banyak, asin dan bumbu terasa, cuma ya agak pricy 58 rebu per porsi. 3 of 5. Nasi ikan bakar filet, rasa standar lah ya. Ikannya cakalang 3 potong dengan kecap berlimpah2, yang gak suka manis jangan pesan. Harga 28 ribu. 3 of 5. Es jeruk. Biasa banget, jeruknya terasa cuma ya gitu, apa sih yang diharapkan dari es jeruk. Harga 10 ribu. 3 of 5. Servis : datang pada saat sepi, pramusaji gercep. Dari pesan sampai makanan datang 15 menit. Cukup komunikatif. 4 of 5. Ada gazebo pinggir pantai yang bisa dipakai customer jika pesan lebih dari 350 ribu. Kalau mau makan di pinggir pantai dengan tenda2 juga bisaaaa. Overall 3 of 5. Tapi kalau lapar di pantai ini, mending kesini daripada di gambling makan di warung2 makan ramdom yang gak tau harga dan rasanya. Will be back kalo kesini dan ngepasi laper.
review_translated_text: Parking: the same as Indrayanti beach parking, spacious and enough to fit a car. 4 of 5. Location and atmosphere: right on Indrayanti beach so you can enjoy the beach breeze and the viem while eating. 5 of 5. Food : Order the salted egg fried squid. Delicious, but not the best one. Large portion, tastes salty and seasoned, but its a bit pricey, 58 thousand per portion. 3 of 5. Filet grilled fish rice, standard taste. The fish is 3 pieces of skipjack with lots of soy sauce. If you dont like sweets, dont order it. Price 28 thousand. 3 of 5. Orange juice. Very ordinary, the orange tastes just like that, what do you expect from orange ice. Price 10 thousand. 3 of 5. Service: come when its quiet, the waiter is fast. From ordering until the food came 15 minutes. Quite communicative. 4 of 5. There is a beachside gazebo that customers can use if their order is more than 350 thousand. If you want to eat on the beach in tents, thats also possible. Overall 3 out of 5. But if youre hungry on this beach, its better to come here rather than gamble on eating at random food stalls that dont know the price or taste. Will be back if I come here and satisfy my hunger.

review_text: Ini pantai virall yg mempelopori wisata pantai di gunungkidul menjadi ramai.. sebelum ada pantai indrayanti pantai2 lainnya blm begitu viral.. nama asli pantai ini adalah pantai pulang sawal.. karena ada restorannya pak Indra dan bu yanti makanya di Sebut pantai indrayanti.. disini kita bisa pesan makanan dan minuman.. aku pesan kerang hijau banyak yang kering mungkin stok kemarin.. kelapa muda di gazebo yg bisa kita pakai..  beberapa pedagang setempat menjajakan sovenir.. kalo kesini belilah.. bantu dapur mereka ngebul.. pasir pantainya joss.. disini kita bisa sewa foto tarifnya 40 foto per 100rb.. tp kmrn sy smp 615 foto dan untungnya harganya masih bisa di tawar lebih seperempatnya.. hasil fotonya bagus dan bisa kita pindah ke HP..
review_translated_text: This is the viral beach that pioneered beach tourism in Gunungkidul which became very busy.. before Indrayanti Beach, the other beaches werent so viral.. the original name of this beach was Pulang Sawal Beach.. because there was a restaurant, Mr. Indra and Mrs. Yanti, thats why it was called Indrayanti Beach.. here we can order food and drinks.. I ordered green mussels, lots of them are dry, maybe yesterdays stock.. young coconuts in the gazebo that we can use.. several local traders selling souvenirs.. if you come here, buy them.. help them in the kitchen.. the sand on the beach joss.. here we can rent photos at a rate of 40 photos per 100 thousand.. but now I have 615 photos and luckily the price can still be negotiated for more than a quarter... the photos are good and we can move to a cellphone..

review_text: If I can give no star I would. First we arrive asking for table they said they are full, but we saw the tables are empty. They said its reserved, alright so we find the table at terrace. The service was super bad, we have arrived 1:30pm, and asked for deposit 500 for 5 people (which is alright) but then they told us we only can order by 2:30pm. We said ok no problem, but then at 2:30 we want to order they said still cant order because they are busy cooking for the 20people who already reserved the table( FYI those 20people have not arrive yet, even late for their appointment). So I ask for the manager, they said manager is not around I ask for the assistant manager or supervisor also they are not around, again I ask who is on duty today, they said no one. They prefer to serve ghosts that dont know where they are yet rather than the customer who already in the restaurant and also already paid. I dont understand how come this kind of restaurant has a very bad service, this is the worse I ever had in my experience. You take the money but u starve us. If you served us, we would already be done eating before your ghosts guest arrived. If you cant manage a restaurant please just close it down. You are wasting our time and energy. So disappointed. Even after we left their ghost guests hasnt show up. We ended up left and starved.
Harga makanan elit, rasa biasa. Pelayanan yang kurang cepat dan tepat, harus ditambahkan karyawan, terutama saat hari liburan. Suasananya jelas keren dan mantap.
review_translated_text: Elite food prices, ordinary taste. If service is not fast and accurate, additional employees must be added, especially during holidays. The atmosphere is clearly cool and steady.

review_translated_text: The good thing is that when you want to go in there is a notification.. You pay 100 thousand to enter and you can exchange it for a food voucher.. If 4 people are finished, its 400 thousand to enter.. We prefer the stall next door... 80 thousand is enough for all 4 of us.

review_text: 2 kali aku ke sini. Kalo ke jogja dan ke pantai pasti ke sini karena emang nyari tempat, cafe yg semi private dan bersih. Trus nginepnya di casa coco. Emang bukan yg suka main air tp suka nongkrongnya aja hehe. Anak2ku bisa main pasir, trus emak bapaknya nungguin di cafe. Untuk harga makanan dan rasanya cukup lahh, overall good. Bagus ya foto3 pas belom rame.
review_translated_text: Ive been here twice. If you go to Jogja and the beach, definitely come here because you are looking for a place, a cafe that is semi-private and clean. Then I stayed at Casa Coco. Im not really a fan of playing in water but I just like hanging out hehe. My children can play in the sand, then their mother and father wait at the cafe. For the price of the food and the taste, its quite good, overall good. Its good to take photos when its not busy yet.

review_text: Cafe and Bar yang ada private beach nya. Masuk kesini 1 orang dewasa minimal order 100.000, untuk anak-anak minimal order 50.000 Suasananya nyaman, sayang kesini saat mendung. Rasa makanan pizzanya enak, yang lain standar

review_text: Tepatnya nyaman dan teduh banget Service nya jg bagus karyawannya ramah ramah Makanannya untuk Cafe di pesisir sudah enak dan fresh. Followup costumers juga bagus Kalo ke sini Gunungkidul bakal main lg sih ke sini Harga jg worth it

review_text: Food was actually pretty terrible for the exorbitant price. I ordered Spaghetti Aglio Olio and it came out sloppy. My sister ordered Chicken Fried Rice and it was a bit better in presentation than my order at least. The iced tea is pretty expe, 25K/cup for a tea bag quality cup of tea  They dont even charge that much for sweet ice tea in pricy cafes in BALI The cafe isnt as well maintained as it seems. Those travel influencers glorifed it a lil too much so lower your expectation. The views are pretty but I wonder if its worth the hefty price with mediocre food in return? The deal breaker, however, isnt all the things I mentioned above. Its actually some of the staffs behavior. I overheard them talking about their customers behind their back in javanese thinking they wouldnt understand? I was about to leave and wondered if they were talking about me because some of their descriptions matched our circumstances HAHAH  Not a great look for the business.

Saya ke sini di hari Minggu dan ternyata baru buka jam 11 tidak sesuai informasi di instagram. Begitu masuk akan dii fokan minimal pembelian per org 100k, kalo bersedia dengan yg diinfokan silakan masuk dan harus menyerahkan deposit awal 200k. Area kursi, bean bag dan jaring free kecuali gazebo harus bayar sewa 30k. Untuk suasana, overall biasa saja hanya menjual pemandangan menghadap laut, tidak harus masuk ke sini jika mau cukup berada di pantai di bawahnya. Makananya enak, tapi biasa saja. Hanya saja harga makanan & minumannya yg overprice kalau menurut saya. Sekelas air mineral Cleo harganya 30k belum ppn10%+5% service. Harga minuman paling murah 23k untuk Lemontea. Untuk harga makanan side dish 35-55k. Buat maincourse >55k Kalau yg mau menikmati pemandangan saran saya ke sini sore sambil menunggu sunset.
review_translated_text: I came here on Sunday and apparently it only opened at 11 oclock, not according to the information on Instagram. As soon as you enter you will be asked for a minimum purchase per person of 100k, if you are happy with what you have been told, please enter and must submit an initial deposit of 200k. The chair area, bean bags and nets are free except for the gazebo, you have to pay 30k to rent. As for the atmosphere, overall its just normal, it only sells views facing the sea, you dont have to go here if you want to just be on the beach below. The food is delicious, but ordinary. Its just that the prices of food & drinks are overpriced in my opinion. A class of Cleo mineral water costs 30k without 10% VAT + 5% service. The cheapest drink price is 23k for Lemontea. The price for side dishes is 35-55k. Make maincourse >55k If you want to enjoy the view, my advice is to come here in the afternoon while waiting for the sunset.

review_text: I recently visited this cozy hangout spot and had a mixed experience. Overall, it offers a comfortable environment with delicious food at reasonable prices, but there were a few drawbacks that need addressing. Pros: Delicious Food Menu at Affordable Prices: One of the standout features of this place is the diverse and tasty food menu. The dishes are reasonably priced, making it an excellent option for students and budget-conscious individuals. Clean and Relaxed Atmosphere: The ambiance is pleasing, with a clean and well-maintained dining area that sets the stage for a pleasant dining experience. Its an ideal place to unwind and enjoy a meal with friends and family. Sufficient Car Parking: The availability of ample parking space is a big advantage, ensuring convenience for visitors who come by car. In-house Prayer Area: The presence of a designated prayer area behind the restaurant is a thoughtful addition, making it convenient for those who wish to offer their prayers while dining. Good Service: The staff was attentive and provided prompt service, enhancing the overall dining experience. Cons: Lack of Free Wi-Fi: Unfortunately, the establishment does not provide free Wi-Fi access, which can be a drawback for customers who rely on the internet while dining. Noisy Location: The restaurants proximity to a busy road causes some noise disturbance, making it less suitable for those seeking a tranquil environment. Limited Electrical Outlets: One major inconvenience was the scarcity of power outlets for charging devices. More electrical outlets should be made available to cater to the needs of customers, especially those who want to work or study while dining. In conclusion, this hangout spot offers delicious food, a pleasant atmosphere, and ample car parking, making it a great choice for various occasions. Students, in particular, will find the affordable menu prices appealing. The availability of a prayer area also adds to its appeal for certain customers. However, improvements such as providing free Wi-Fi, addressing the noise issue, adding more electrical outlets, and enhancing the evening lighting are essential to elevate the overall customer experience. If these concerns are addressed, it will undoubtedly become an even more popular spot for dining and hanging out.

review_translated_text: A place to hang out in the middle of the city that carries the twilight concept 1. Strategic location and easy to access, close to Tugu station and bus stop 2. The space is spacious, on the 1st floor the place is air-conditioned and cozy so its suitable for just resting or doing work, on the 2nd floor the place is not air-conditioned and there is a balcony so you can see the view of Mangkubumi Street from above 3. The types of drinks are also varied and the taste is good, but the glasses are made of plastic and the size is small 4. The price is quite reasonable because it is in the middle of the city 5. The waiters are also friendly, whether via chat or coming in person Overall still satisfactory

review_text: Cafe yang cocok untuk ngobrol-ngobrol santai dengan teman. Interiornya cantik dan instagramable banget. Temoatnya juga cozy, lokasinya di area tugu, pas kalau mau sambil jalan-jalan di sekitar tugu dan malioboro. Kalau untuk ngerjain tugas sepertinya tidak terlalu cocok, karena sulit menemukan colokan disini, tidak disemua tempat duduk ada colokan listriknya, kalaupun ada hanya ada 1 slot saja. Kalau mau nugas tanpa membutuhkan colokan listrik cocok-cocok aja. Untuk makanan dan minumannya rasanya cukup standart untuk ukuran cafe-cafe di Jogja. Pelayanan nya ramah.
review_translated_text: A cafe that is suitable for relaxing chats with friends. The interior is beautiful and very instagrammable. The place is also cozy, the location is in the monument area, perfect if you want to take a walk around the monument and Malioboro. If its for doing work, it doesnt seem very suitable, because its hard to find a plug here, not all the seats have an electric plug, even if there is, theres only 1 slot. If you want to do work without needing an electrical outlet, thats fine. The food and drinks taste quite standard for cafes in Jogja. The service is friendly.

review_text: Ada yg baru tempat Ngopi di Jl Mangkubumi / Margoutomo. Tepatnya Depan Hotel Harper. Tempat strategis dan dalam Kawasan Sumbu Filosofi. Deket Tugu atau Malioboro. Saat masuk kedalam, Dinginnya kerasa. Cocok buat ngopi2 santai ataupun nyambi kerjaan. Disetiap meja disediakan colokan listrik. Selain Indoor ada juga outdoor yg bisa buat ngerokok santai. Ada 2 lantai. Di lantai atas bisa lihat langsunh jalan mangku bumi. Parking: Lokasi parkir yg cukup gampang disepanjang Jalan Margoutomo.
review_translated_text: There is a new coffee place on Jl Mangkubumi / Margoutomo. Exactly in front of the Harper Hotel. Strategic location and in the Philosophy Axis Area. Near Tugu or Malioboro. When you go inside, it feels cold. Suitable for relaxing coffee or work. Each table is provided with an electric socket. Apart from indoor, there is also outdoor where you can smoke casually. There are 2 floors. On the top floor you can see Jalan Mangku Bumi directly. Parking: The parking location is quite easy along Jalan Margoutomo.

review_text: If youre looking for a laid-back spot in the heart of Yogya, look no further than Nyore  Coffee and Space. Conveniently located just a 500 meters away from Yogya Station and 300 meters Tugu Yogya, this cafe is the ultimate hangout spot for kicking back and chillin with your friends. Room: The cafes vibe is on point with two floors. Whether you prefer chilling indoors or soaking up the sun in the outdoor area, youll find comfy seating options like plush sofas and wooden chairs. Plus, the AC keeps things nice and cool, even on the hottest days. WiFi: Staying connected is a must with their reliable WiFi, so you can Instagram your foods or catch up on TikTok trends while sipping your favorite brew. Restroom: Clean and well-maintained bathrooms available. Mushola: For those in need of praying, theres a clean and proper mushola in the outdoor area. Food & Beverages: The food and beverages are good, like usual cafe standard, but the menu could do with a bit more variety :( Overall, this cafe ticks all the boxes for a relaxed and enjoyable cafe experience in Yogya. Whether youre catching up with friends or doing WFC, this cafe is sure to become your new favorite spot.

We entered this place without expectations looking for a coffee with ice and air conditioning. The place is nice, comfortable, and from the coffee we ordered we can say that we were pleasantly surprised! The Javanese coffee was AMAZING, the avocado coffee was very good, and the jack fruit coffee was good. While the price may seem expensive compared to other places in Indonesia, the java coffee is worth every penny you pay for it.
review_translated_text: Entramos a este lugar sin espectativas buscando un cafe con hielo y aire acondicionado. El lugar esta lindo, comodo, y de los cafe que pedimos podemos decir que fuimos gratamente sorprendidos! El cafe javanese estaba ESPECTACULAR, el cafe con palta/aguacate estaba muy rico, y el cafe con jack fruit estaba bien. Si bien el precio puede parecer caro respecto a otros lugares de Indonesia, el cafe de java vale cada centavo que pagas por el.

review_text: I found this cafe while looking for a restaurant that accepts credit card payments. The interior space was spacious, the staff responded well, and it was clean. As for the food, I thought it was sadly greasy and the portions were a bit small. I ordered two pieces of nasi goreng/pasta, and even though I dont eat a lot of pasta, I thought it wasnt enough...   The nasi goreng was seasoned well and was good. There was a lot of oil in it, so there were traces left on the plate. The price is not cheap, but I hope it improves a little.

Dekat sekali dengan tugu jogja, hanya 300an meter. Suasana tidak ramai meski lagi liburan lebaran. Jadi asik tidak berisik dan bejubel. Mungkin orang pikir disini mahal padahal masih standar harganya. Pilihan tempat duduknya juga cukup variatif, ada sofa, beanbag, kursi santai, kursi makan. Tempatnya luas, ada indoor dan outdoor. Instagramable juga buat yang hobi foto. Bisa parkir motor maupun mobil, karena memang dipinggir jalan. Sayangnya beberap minuman dingin disajikannya pakai gelas plastik yang tentunya kurang ramah lingkungan, apalagi klo tidak dikelola dengan baik. Sedotan sih tulisannya udah oxo biodegradable, tapi tahu juga ya beneran bisa cepet terurai atau cuma labelnya aja.
review_translated_text: Very close to the Jogja monument, only 300 meters. The atmosphere was not crowded even though it was the Eid holiday. So its cool not to be noisy and busy. Maybe people think its expensive here even though the prices are still standard. The seating options are also quite varied, there are sofas, beanbags, lounge chairs, dining chairs. The place is spacious, there is indoor and outdoor. Instagramable also for those who like photos. You can park motorbikes and cars, because it is on the side of the road. Unfortunately, some cold drinks are served in plastic cups which are certainly not environmentally friendly, especially if they are not managed properly. The straw says it is oxo biodegradable, but do you know whether it really can decompose quickly or is it just the label?

review_translated_text: Found this place, initially from maps. Keep looking at social media, how come you like the place hahaha. Its a bit difficult to find this place, even though its on the side of a big road. But the words Metemu Kopi are too small, plus the meeting location is a bit inside (past another house). Parking is very spacious, cars are safe. Service okay When I came in... MasyaAllah I really liked it. The interior has more of a modern Javanese atmosphere. There are lots of paintings, displays, antique motorbikes, etc. The chairs are still very Javanese, some are modern. As for the outdoor area, the theme is more like a garden. And very beautiful... There arent enough prayer rooms... Even though there are mukenas and prayer mats. But in my opinion, a better place to pray is directly on the floor. No need for plywood like that. Because it makes you uncomfortable, youre afraid you wont be strong, etc... Menu review: The menu here is quite medium... Actually, its okay, if you follow the quality and quantity. However, I was a bit disappointed. I didnt take a photo, because I didnt feel good, and its true....wkwkwk I ordered several menus: 1. Onion rings The onions use flour which is usually used for fried foods. This means its not coated in the special flour that is usually found in onion rings. Where there is no feeling anymore. You should add a little seasoning to the flour 4.5/10 2. Tempeh Meet/tempeh mendoan (22k) Huh 22k with taste and portion like that???? Not really!!! Bland taste. The tempeh is cut into small and thin pieces, contains 4. 5/10 So my conclusion... I like this place to hang out for a long time, because the atmosphere of the place is really good. But hanging around for a long time with the quality of the menu like that...its a bit sad, isnt it? Come on, please pay attention to the taste and portions

review_text: Lokasi makan dengan mengusung konsep cukup unik menurut saya. Konsep bahari yang membawa kita seakan berada di dalam kapal yang sedang berlayar, dengan pemandangan lanskap aliran sungai progo sendiri melengkapi konsep ini. Segala pernak-pernak seperti di kapal, furniture lainnya dengan bahan kayu, beberapa meja berbentuk kapal, namun juga ada furniture dengan hiasan modern seperti menambah daya imajinasi kita seperti sedang menikmati sajian nikmat ala diatas kapal. Fasilitasnya menurut saya sudah cukup membuat nyaman kita sehingga memilih lokasi ini jadi spot makan keluarga, grub, atau santai dengan teman. Namun untuk grub atau keluarga sebaiknya reservasi dahulu, mengingat moment penting perlu direncanakan dan diutamakan kenyamanannya dalam memilih spot terbaik kita yg ada di restauran ini Menu resto nya sendiri bervariasi, cocok untuk segala jenis penikmat. Karena dari yang Nusantara (Jogja banget), asia, sampai western disini ada. Dan tipe makanannya yang tersedia banyak, mulai dari savory dish hingga dessert. Minumannanya juga ada perkopian dan perjusan, namun ada juga air mineral untuk si original. Selain itu, ternyata ada paket Jeep tour juga. Bisa di tanyakan langsung dengan pengelolanya, sedang rate harga saya rasa sudah banyak yg uploud di sini bisa dijadikan referensi karena saya lihat tidak ada perubahan harga (lihat foto terbaru). Rate HTM nya cukup okay dengan rasa, suasana, fasilitas, dan pemandangan yang ditawarkan. Oiya, sekadar informasi disini juga tersedia wifi ya kalau mau connect bisa diinfokan ke staff yang ada disana dan terkadang ada music nya juga. Parking: Sediakan uang pas aja yang mau anda kasihi ke mereka, karena kadang kang parkirnya bilang gak ada kembalian ternyata ada ehe
review_translated_text: In my opinion, this dining location has quite a unique concept. A nautical concept that makes us feel like we are on a sailing ship, with views of the landscape of the Progo River itself, complements this concept. All the knick-knacks are like on a ship, other furniture made of wood, some tables shaped like a ship, but there is also furniture with modern decoration which adds to our imagination as if we were enjoying a delicious meal on a ship. In my opinion, the facilities are enough to make us comfortable so we chose this location as a spot for family dining, grubbing or relaxing with friends. However, for groups or families, its best to make a reservation first, remembering that important moments need to be planned and comfort must be prioritized in choosing our best spots in this restaurant The restaurant menu itself is varied, suitable for all types of diners. Because from the archipelago (Jogja really), Asia, to the West, we have them here. And there are many types of food available, from savory dishes to desserts. The drinks also include coffee and juice, but there is also mineral water for the original. Apart from that, it turns out there is a Jeep tour package too. You can ask the manager directly, as for the price rate, I think many have uploaded it here, which can be used as a reference because I see there has been no change in price (see latest photo). The HTM rate is quite okay with the taste, atmosphere, facilities and views on offer. Oh yes, just for information, there is also wifi available here, so if you want to connect you can let the staff there know and sometimes there is music too. Parking: Just provide the exact amount of money you want to give them, because sometimes the parking lot says theres no change, but it turns out there is, hehe.

review_text: -Bagi Kopi Prawirotaman- Saya datang ke kedai kopi ini sekitar jam 12 malam lebih. Kebetulan, saya menginap di daerah penginapan sekitar belakang pasar Prawirotaman jalan kaki menuju kedai ini. Awalnya mau cari makanan dan kopi terdekat, rekomendasi dari maps yang buka sampai jam 3 subuh ya cuman Bagi Kopi ini. Ketika datang, dengan rasa cukup capek dan lapar keadaan mati listrik. Malam sabtu, dan suasana sangat ramai mahasiswa yg sedang mengerjakan tugas. Terlihat dari banyak buku dan leptop di atas meja mereka. Ketika hendak pesan, tertulis close order sampai jam 1 malam. Hampir saja ku balik badan utk makan nasgor atau sate di pinggir jalan tadi. Namun, karena males jalan balik, saya dan temen menunggu hingga jam 1 dini hari. Menunggu pesanan pun cukup lama belum lagi ditambah waktu menunggu open order yang sekitar 30mnt. Untuk harga standar, rasa kopi juga standar sesuai dengan harga. Klo tidak salah kisaran 18-20an. Sialnya, saya belum bisa pesan makanan berat karena alasan lain hal. Sudah menunggu sekitar 30mnt dan yang saya pesan tetap cemilan saja. Rasa cemilan pun kurang enak, mungkin karena perut yang sudah tidak nyaman menahan lapar dan malah minum kopi. Untung saja tidak mual. Suasana nyaman, luas dan cukup bersih. Kenapa cukup bersih, karena meja yg saya duduki itu masih banyak sampah bekas pelanggan sebelumnya. AC juga tidak terlalu dingin, pdahal indoor dan sudah dini hari. Ada ruangan outdoor yang berasap tebal seperti pembakaran sesuatu. Parkiran juga cukup luas, biaya parkir tentunya ada. Karena jalan kaki jadi tidak perlu membayar parkir. Overall, cukup menyesal datang ke sini karena niat hati chill sambil makan yang ada malah gaenak perut. Tapi tempat ini cocok banget bagi kalian yang mau nugas ramean, karena memang tempat ini mungkin didesain utk mereka yang mau nugas di cafe. Semoga bermanfaat.
review_translated_text: -Share Prawirotaman Coffee- I came to this coffee shop around 12 oclock at night. Coincidentally, I was staying in the accommodation area around the back of Prawirotaman market on foot to this shop. Initially I wanted to look for food and coffee nearby, the recommendation from maps was that it was open until 3 in the morning, just for this coffee. When he arrived, he felt quite tired and hungry and there was a power outage. Saturday night, and the atmosphere was very busy with students doing their assignments. You can see the many books and laptops on their tables. When I wanted to order, it said close orders until 1 pm. I almost turned around to eat nasgor or satay on the side of the road. However, because we were too lazy to go back, my friend and I waited until 1 in the morning. Waiting for orders was quite long, not to mention the waiting time for open orders, which was around 30 minutes. For standard prices, the taste of coffee is also standard according to the price. If Im not mistaken, its around 18-20. Unfortunately, I havent been able to order heavy food for other reasons. Ive been waiting for about 30 minutes and what I ordered was just snacks. The taste of the snacks wasnt very good, perhaps because the stomach was uncomfortable holding back hunger and instead drank coffee. Luckily I didnt get nauseous. The atmosphere is comfortable, spacious and quite clean. Why is it quite clean, because the table I sat at still had lots of rubbish from previous customers. The AC was also not very cold, even though it was indoors and it was early in the morning. There was an outdoor room that had thick smoke like something was burning. Parking is also quite spacious, of course there are parking fees. Because its walking distance, theres no need to pay for parking. Overall, I regret coming here because I had the intention of chilling while eating something that didnt make my stomach happy. But this place is really suitable for those of you who want to work at a party, because this place is probably designed for those who want to work at a cafe. Hope it is useful.

review_translated_text: Quite often I stop by Pajama Cafe just to do my homework. The place is super cozy, whether outdoor or indoor. Its as nice and comfortable as it is for doing assignments. Super calming and not noisy. The sound of the music is soft, so you dont feel disturbed when youre working. The beverages prices are cafe standard, but the ala carte prices are hotel standard. Not surprised because its the same hotel. The baristas are friendly! There are many variations of drinks, the taste is all good. Never disappointed. I really like strawberry matcha, shaken berry, virgin mojito, and kawista punch (because Im coffee intolerant hehe). You also have to try the ala carte style, especially since the katsu sambal matah and Japanese katsu curry are so delicious. Its a bit pricey, but its worth trying and you wont regret it. Huge appreciation to his entire fnb team! Next time I will stop by again if I have free time to just unwind.

The ambiance is perfect for anyone needing to concentrate or just relax after a long day. With its quirky yet minimalist art decor, the cafe offers a unique vibe thats both inviting and inspiring. The first thing youll notice is the warm lighting and the comfortable seating arrangements, ranging from personal tables to cozy couches, ideal for solo visitors or groups. The large windows provide plenty of natural light during the day and a peaceful view of the evening sky. As a digital nomad, I appreciate the stable Wi-Fi connection and the ample power outlets available at almost every table. The staff seems to understand the need for uninterrupted work time, as they serve with a smile and maintain a respectful distance unless called upon.

review_text: The place is beautiful. An old repurposed colonial era building with the least amount of facelift possible giving it a nostalgic ambience. But the service for the love of god is unbelievably slow despite me being the only patron dining there at the time. Almost an hour for a simple wrap and chicken wings, which could have been improved had the salad not been drenched in bottled thousand island and the wings better marinated as the seasoning seemed to merely stick to the outer layer of each wing. Anyways, price is on the affordable side and there s a cute cat that does the zoomies all afternoon as well as a somewhat stable wifi connection so if you just want to work in peace and drink cold coffee here is your sign to go

Coffeeshop ini memiliki mesin roasting sendiri untuk beans produksi mereka,menarik kan. Untuk spotnya ada indoor dibagian depan dan spot outdoor di bagian belakang dengan beberapa pepohonan. Saya lebih suka area outdoornya yang bisa buat santai bersama teman-teman karena lebih luas dibanding area indoornya. Untuk menu sangat lengkap, saya kesini pesan mocktail yang based nya espresso dengan nama Morning Call, rasanya asam manis dan segar, cocok diminum di cuaca panas siang hari.
review_translated_text: Decade of Coffee Roaster - Jogja A coffee shop with a classic building facade and a vintage interior, when we enter this coffee shop it will feel like we have entered an old Dutch house. This coffee shop has its own roasting machine for their beans, interesting, right? There are indoor spots at the front and outdoor spots at the back with several trees. I prefer the outdoor area where you can relax with friends because it is wider than the indoor area. For a very complete menu, I ordered a mocktail here based on espresso called Morning Call, it tastes sweet and sour and fresh, suitable to drink in hot weather during the day.

review_text: Tempat ngopi di kampung Jogoyudan,  perkampungan di pinggir kali Code. Untuk sampai sini masuk ke Jalan Jogoyudan kemudian turun tangga ketika bertemu dengan papan nama co fams. Minuman favoritku di sini untuk yang dingin tame impala dan ramones. Untuk yang hangat choco hazelnut. Harga minuman dari 5 rb untuk kopi tubruk dan yang paling mahal 16 rb untuk kategori signature. Selain jual minuman, Co Fams juga menjual kaset. Jam buka dari jam 16.00 - 00.00. Untuk pengumuman buka tidaknya atau perubahan jadwal buka bisa dicek di story ig @co.famsyk Untuk sepeda motor bisa diparkir di atas, di sebelah tangga. Tapi tidak tersedia tempat untuk parkir mobil
review_translated_text: Coffee place in Jogoyudan village, a village on the edge of the Code river. To get here, enter Jalan Jogoyu and then go down the stairs when you meet the Co Fams sign. My favorite drink here for the cold tame impala and ramones. For warm chocolate hazelnut. Drink prices start from 5 thousand for brewed coffee and the most expensive is 16 thousand for the signature category. Apart from selling drinks, Co Fams also sells cassettes. Opening hours from 16.00 - 00.00. For announcements on whether or not it is open or changes to the opening schedule, you can check the ig story @co.famsyk Motorbikes can be parked above, next to the stairs. But there is no place to park a car

review_text: Nice place, korean/ Japanese tangga vibes. Tempat tenang di perkampungan padat Kali Code. Buka jam 16.00 , jadwal buka - tidaknya di update di story Instagramnya, jadi sebelum kesana cek jadwal buka di story IG nya biar tidak kecelik.
review_translated_text: Nice place, Korean/ Japanese staircase vibes. A quiet place in the busy village of Kali Code. Opens at 16.00, the opening schedule is updated on the Instagram story, so before going there, check the opening schedule on the IG story so you dont get cheated.

review_text: Indonesian diverse varieties of foods never cease to amuse us. Broaden our adventure a bit to explore the Chinatown in Yogyakarta that has long been undiscovered, we get to Kranggan and we slip out a bit towards the southern part of the busy street. We found this Hong Kong Street Food. Humble owners greet us with very nice smiles and the great fragrance of Chinese spices. We ordered Hainan Rice and Chilli oil noodles, as a side dish, we ordered wonton soup. Everything was greeat. Wonton Soup that was served here is very warm, not just the temperature but the characteristics of the flavour. Full of spices, not too salty. Hainan Chicken Rice portion is very generous but not too much, its such an explosions of flavours. The chicken is tender and we also got charsiu version. Definitely must try. Noodle was amazing beyond expectations, tender, sweet sour and salty. One of the best. Overall this resto is 100 Chinese points.

review_text: Tentang Hong Kong Street Foods, saya rasa not bad. Lumayanlah! Warung makan ini menjadi salah satu alternatif untuk menikmati kuliner khas Hong Kong. Tak banyak jumlahnya di Jogja. Apalagi katanya pemiliknya sekaligus yang masak memang asli Hong Kong. Secara masakan memang tidak bisa dibilang wow, istimewa. Tapi bolehlah untuk mencicip menu Hong Kong. Masakannya standar dan edible. Yang bisa saya rekomendasikan adalah Wonton Sup yang gurih, panas, dan terasa enak. Sedangkan makanan yang lainnya cenderung seleranya berbeda. Sayangnya, ekspetasi saya dengan xiao long pao dan dim sum terlalu tinggi, karena nyatanya kecil dan terlalu kenyal; sehingga kurang memuaskan. Untuk minumannya cukup beragam, termasuk minuman panas dan dingin. Tempatnya memang kecil dengan meja dan kursi yang terbatas. Namun, cukup untuk 10 orang maksimal. Tempat kurang nyaman tapi paling tidak relatif tertata dan bersih. Dekorasinya cukup membantu dengan foto-foto tokoh perfilman Hong Kong seperti Bruce Lee dan Andy Lau, dengan satu gambar kota Hong Kong dari atas bukit. Lumayanlah menghadirkan suasana HK. Mungkin bisa diputar lagu-lagu Cantonese yang popular supaya vibe-nya lebih terasa. Harga makanan dan minuman terjangkau. Tidak mahal, tidak juga murah. Pas harganya. Pesannya juga mudah menggunakan kode angka dan menuliskannya di kertas. Secara lokasi, tempat makan ini mudah ditemukan, tepat di sebelah chinese resto Pasar Baru yang sudah lama di Jalan Diponegoro. Cukup dekat dari Tugu Jogja dan Pasar Kranggan. Parkir di depannya bisa, yaitu parkir sejajar tapi terbatas hanya sedikit mobil dan motor, sehingga paling enak kalau naik Gocar atau Grabcar. Parking: Parkir sejajar untuk maksimal 2 mobil di depan warung makan.
review_translated_text: About Hong Kong Street Foods, I dont think its bad. Not bad! This food stall is an alternative way to enjoy typical Hong Kong culinary delights. There are not many of them in Jogja. Moreover, he said that the owner and cook are actually from Hong Kong. In terms of cooking, it cant be said to be wow, special. But its okay to try the Hong Kong menu. The food is standard and edible. What I can recommend is Wonton Soup which is savory, hot and tastes delicious. Meanwhile, other foods tend to have different tastes. Unfortunately, my expectations with the xiao long pao and dim sum were too high, because they were small and too chewy; so its less than satisfying. The drinks are quite varied, including hot and cold drinks. The place is small with limited tables and chairs. However, it is enough for a maximum of 10 people. The place is less comfortable but at least it is relatively organized and clean. The decoration is quite helpful with photos of Hong Kong film figures such as Bruce Lee and Andy Lau, with one picture of Hong Kong city from the top of the hill. Not bad for bringing the HK atmosphere. Maybe you can play popular Cantonese songs so that the vibe is more pronounced. Food and drink prices are affordable. Not expensive, not cheap either. The price is right. The message is also easy to use a number code and write it on paper. In terms of location, this place to eat is easy to find, right next to the old Chinese restaurant Pasar Baru on Jalan Diponegoro. Quite close to Tugu Jogja and Kranggan Market. Parking in front is possible, namely parallel parking but limited to only a few cars and motorbikes, so its best if you take a Gocar or Grabcar. Parking: Parallel parking for a maximum of 2 cars in front of the food stall.

TLDR ; Good for chat and work, there is plenty of space and the menu is good. Review Lokio Cafe Tempat 5/5 Bertempat di Jalan Mangkubumi, Lokio Cafe mudah di akses. Tempat parkir berada di trotoar jalan yang lumayan luas, jadi bisa datang menggunakan mobil. Terdapat tiga bagian tempat duduk, yang pertama berada di luar, di samping trotoar. Yang kedua berada di lantai dua yaitu indoor ber AC, dan yang ketiga yaitu rooftop. Ruangan indoor mempunyai banyak kursi, cocok untuk digunakan bekerja. Sedangkan rooftop lebih cocok digunakan sebagai tempat mengobrol di senja atau malam karena sangat panas saat siang. Menu 4/5 Harga menu di kisaran 27k, harga yang standar untuk kafe yang berada di inti kota Jogja. Namun Lokio Cafe punya promo pagi dan bundling yang menarik bagi saya, jadi saya bisa menikmati suasana kota Jogja tanpa harus membayar mahal. Saya pesan Cafe Latte yang awalnya 27k menjadi 18k, menurut saya rasanya standar. Pelayanan 5/5 Pegawai ramah dan cakap dalam menjelaskan menu dan promo. Kamar Mandi 4/5 Kamar mandi lebar dan tidak bau. Namun drainase kurang bersih, lampu remang-remang dan gagang pintu luar rusak.
review_translated_text: TLDR ; Good for chat and work, there is plenty of space and the menu is good. Lokio Cafe Review Place 5/5 Located on Jalan Mangkubumi, Lokio Cafe is easy to access. The parking lot is on the sidewalk which is quite wide, so you can come by car. There are three seating sections, the first is outside, next to the sidewalk. The second is on the second floor, which is indoor with AC, and the third is on the rooftop. The indoor room has lots of chairs, suitable for working. Meanwhile, the rooftop is more suitable as a place to chat at dusk or at night because it is very hot during the day. Menu 4/5 Menu prices are around 27k, a standard price for cafes in the core of Jogja. However, Lokio Cafe has morning promotions and bundling that are attractive to me, so I can enjoy the atmosphere of Jogja without having to pay a fortune. I ordered a Cafe Latte which was originally 27k to 18k, in my opinion the taste was standard. Service 5/5 The employees are friendly and competent in explaining the menu and promotions. Bathroom 4/5 The bathroom is wide and doesnt smell bad. However, the drainage is not clean, the lights are dim and the outside door handle is broken.

response_from_owner_text: Ibu Susy Djaha yang terhormat, Karena Anda menulis ulasan atas nama anak Anda, sayangnya ada beberapa hal yang tidak benar. Berikut ini adalah apa yang terjadi : Seperti yang Anda lihat di profil Google kami, dapur tutup pada jam 22:30. Anak-anak Anda datang setelah waktu tersebut. Waktu itu di dapur sedang menyelesaikan pesanan terakhir. Pelayan kami mengambil pesanan anak-anak Anda, tetapi kemudian menyadari bahwa sekarang sudah pukul 23:00 dan dapur sudah tutup. Seharusnya dia memeriksa dapur terlebih dahulu, untuk itu kami mohon maaf. Tapi dia tidak bilang bawha Nasi Goreng habis dan kemudian mengubah perkataannya! Kami sangat sedih mendengar bahwa Anda merasa kami tidak ingin melayani anak-anak Anda karena pakaian dan/atau ras mereka. Di Easy Groovy kami menyambut semua orang dan memperlakukan mereka dengan sama tanpa memandang usia, ras, pakaian, jenis kelamin, agama, atau apa pun! Keberagaman sangat penting bagi kami dan ini tercermin dalam tim campuran kami. Kami dengan tulus meminta Anda untuk mempertimbangkan untuk mengubah ulasan Anda atau menghapusnya, karena Anda belum pernah ke sana dan hanya mendengar cerita dari anak-anak Anda. The clothes are worn out and they dont look classy, so my child isnt fit to eat at this cafe? My child wants to eat at T4 this Eid holiday. 11 April 24, on Google I saw that the operating hours were 01.00, my child ate at 23.00. response_from_owner_translated_text: Dear Mrs. Susy Djaha, Since you are writing a review on behalf of your child, unfortunately there are some things that are not true. Here is what happened: As you can see on our Google profile, the kitchen closes at 10:30 p.m. Your children come after that time. At that time in the kitchen finishing the last order. Our waiter takes your kids orders, but then realizes its 11pm and the kitchen is closed. He should have checked the kitchen first, for that we apologize. But he didnt say that the Fried Rice was finished and then change his words! We are deeply saddened to hear that you feel we do not want to serve your children because of their clothing and/or race. At Easy Groovy we welcome everyone and treat them the same regardless of age, race, clothing, gender, religion or anything else! Diversity is very important to us and this is reflected in our mixed team. We sincerely ask you to consider changing your review or removing it, as you have never been there and have only heard stories from your children. Once again, we apologize for forgetting to check the kitchen status before taking your childrens orders

review_text: A Groovy Return to Pawirotaman From Easy Going to Easy Garden, and now Easy Groovy - it seems Yogyakarta cant get enough of your easy vibes! As a happy customer on your Pawirotaman adventure, Im excited to share my experience at the new spot. First things first, location is king, and Easy Groovy nails it. Right across from Gelato on Pawirotaman, its a prime spot for grabbing a bite and a bevvy after a day of exploring. The menu offered a delightful mix of familiar favorites and some intriguing newcomers. We enjoyed good, solid food   juicy burgers, fresh salads, and of course a good beer selection. Those amazing pizzas have left the menu, but enough news to choose from. The juices were a refreshing burst of flavor, and the cold beer hit the spot on a warm Yogyakarta afternoon. Now, opening any new restaurant comes with its challenges, and the hustle and bustle of the first day added to the charm. It was clear the Easy team was working hard to keep everyone happy, and the atmosphere was buzzing with excitement. Overall, Easy Groovy delivers on its promise: easy vibes, good food, and a great location. Its a welcome addition to the Pawirotaman scene, and I cant wait to see what new grooves theyll lay down in the future. Today the staff handled the opening-day rush well! The decor, the music, the overall feeling of the place was comfy. It was casual and a bit laid-back. We want to wish the Easy team success.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Gijs for this absolutely lovely review! We are delighted to hear that you liked our new place and hope you will come back again soon. Yes, we decided to discontinue our famous pizzas but we added many new Mexican dishes and more Indonesian food to our menu.
Thank you sister

review_text: Jadi gini,  Kopi Ramu ini bisa dibilang kopi kekinian kedua yang berada di area Ponjong yang sempat saya coba. Secara rasa saya suka kopi susunya itu pas menurut saya terus harganya juga masih ramah untuk warga Ponjong dan sekitarnya. Menunya juga banyak ada kopi kopi aja variannya banyak kemudian ada non kopi juga ada yang manual apa kayak Vietnam drip dan semacamnya itu juga komplit lah. Saya sendiri mencobanya untuk take away ya jadi dibawa pulang Jadi saya nggak menikmati di lokasi tapi interiornya eksteriornya menarik walaupun mungil tapi ini lumayanlah untuk apa namanya bagi yang hobi kopi kekinian tapi nggak mau ke Wonosari maupun ke Jogja sekarang di Ponjong sudah tersedia. Semoga kedepannya tambah nyaman rasa juga masih dipertahankan kalau bisa rasa kopi susunya itu dibuat seperti Couvee kalau di Jogja itu sangat jos.
review_translated_text: So you see, Kopi Ramu can be said to be the second contemporary coffee in the Ponjong area that I have tried. In terms of taste, I like the milk coffee, its just right, in my opinion, and the price is still friendly for the residents of Ponjong and its surroundings. There are also lots of coffee on the menu, there are lots of coffee variants, then there are non-coffee ones as well as manual ones like Vietnamese drip and the like, they are also complete. I myself tried it for take away so I took it home so I didnt enjoy it at the location but the interior and exterior are attractive even though its small but its not bad for what its called for those who like modern coffee but dont want to go to Wonosari or Jogja, now its available in Ponjong. Hopefully in the future the taste will still be more comfortable and if possible, the milk coffee taste will be made like Couvee in Jogja, which is very delicious.

Mobil&motor bisa masuk.ada akses dari selatan dekat jembatan jalan Sardjito tap hanya bisa di lalui sepeda motor. Parki modor dan mobil memadai. Harga kopi dan makanan murah. Pelayanan ramah dan cepat.
review_translated_text: A relaxing place to hang out while drinking coffee and snacking. Located in the center of Jogja city but with a calm atmosphere, not too noisy. Cars & motorbikes can enter. There is access from the south near the Sardjito road bridge but it can only be used by motorbikes. Adequate motorbike and car parking. Cheap coffee and food prices. Friendly and fast service.
