review_text: Pulang dari perjalanan gunung Kidul ke arah Yogya. Berniat mau ngopi dan makan sedikit sebelum pulang ke Semarang, dan melihat tempat ini serasa mengasyikan berada di depan Tugu Yogya. Namun tidak mengasyikan. Yang saya dan teman2 dapatkan kekecewaan pada pelayanannya 1. Pertama tiba disambut hangat dan ramah oleh kepala restonya. Dan dia menginformasikan bahwa akan tutup jam 00.00 malam. Dan saya datang jam 10.35. Saya tanya masih bisa pesan? Dan masih bisa pesan makan?  Jawab dari Orang yang menyambut : baik, bisa apa saja. Lalu saya meng iyakan. Masuk dan pesan. Karena sudah dibilang sebelumnya last order. Dan bisa pesan. Maka kami pesan. Begitu duduk di lantai 2. Saya pesan Es Kopi ( aeropress) pakai ES pisah.  Namun pegawainya bilang tidak bisa. Yang lain saja. Dia menyarankan menu lain yang tidak saya pesan. Ini membuat kecewa. Trus pesan makan nasi, mie pangsit, dan lain2 mereka jawab tidak tersedia. Trus saya tanya  balik yang ada apa? Dia bilang cuma nasi goreng dan bakmi. Telus pegawainya ga niat daftarin menunya. Pegawainya ada sekitar 3 di atas. Dan sepi. Yang ada prang di balkon. Bukannya tadi di bawah bisa pesan apa aja?? Trus saya kecewa dan meninggalkan tempat tersebut. Padahal sayang tempat bagus, pusat kota, pemandangan Tugu Yogya, cozy. Namun pelayanan buruk. Trus pergi ngopi dan makan di tempat lain. Parking: Nice
review_translated_text: Returning from a trip from Gunung Kidul to Yogya. Intended to have coffee and eat a little before returning to Semarang, and seeing this place felt exciting being in front of the Yogya Monument. But its not fun. What my friends and I were disappointed with was the service 1. When you first arrived, you were greeted warmly and friendly by the head of the restaurant. And he informed that it would close at 00.00 at night. And I came at 10.35. I asked if I could still order? And can you still order food? Answer from the person who greeted: OK, it could be anything. Then I said yes. Log in and order. Because it was said before last order. And you can order. So we ordered. As soon as I sat on the 2nd floor, I ordered Iced Coffee (aeropress) using separate ice. But the employee said he couldnt. Just another one. He suggested another menu that I didnt order. This is disappointing. Then ordering rice, wonton noodles, etc. they said they werent available. Then I asked again what was going on? He said only fried rice and noodles. Telus employees dont intend to list the menu. There are around 3 employees above. And quiet. Theres a man on the balcony. Wasnt it possible to order anything below? Then I was disappointed and left the place. Even though its a shame, the place is nice, city center, view of Tugu Yogya, cozy. But bad service. Then go get coffee and eat somewhere else.

review_text: Tempat ini salah satu tempat yang sudah ke 4x aku datangin di Jogja. Kalo datang di siang hari, cukup banyak varian yang bisa kita temui disini, mulai dari berbagai jenis karbo selain nasi juga ada papeda, kasbi (singkong), bahkan pisang. Pilihan menu utamanya juga banyak, mulai dari beberapa jenis ikan, cumi, juga udang, mulai dari bakar sampai kuah kuning yang begitu match dilidah ketika dipadu dengan sambal Colo-colonya. Sayuran yang disediakan juga gak perlu diragukan lagi rasanya. Beberapa kali aku datang kesini karena rindu Tuna kuah kuning, dan Baracuda bakar, sayur bunga pepaya juga sayur jantung pisang, dan es jeruk. Menu yang selalu aku pesan ketika kesana. Budget yang dikeluarkan juga masih cukup worth it, sekitar 120 ribuan untuk makan kenyang dan pulang dengan bahagia.
review_translated_text: This place is one of the places I have visited 4 times in Jogja. If you come during the day, we can find quite a lot of variants here, starting from various types of carbohydrates besides rice, there are also papeda, kasbi (cassava), even bananas. There are also many main menu choices, ranging from several types of fish, squid, and shrimp, from grilled to yellow sauce which is very pleasing to the tongue when combined with the Colo-colo chili sauce. Theres no need to doubt the taste of the vegetables provided. I came here several times because I missed Tuna in yellow sauce, and grilled Baracuda, papaya flower vegetables and banana flower vegetables, and orange ice. The menu I always order when I go there. The budget spent is still quite worth it, around 120 thousand to eat your fill and go home happy.

review_text: Ke sini dalam rangka buka puasa dadakan keluarga. Manajemennya sumpah kurang bagus. Beberapa meja diberi puding dan air mineral, tapi meja kami kosong tidak diberi apapun sampai pukul setengah 7 minuman baru datang. Itu juga bolak balik mengingatkan kalau meja kami belum ada minum sama sekali. Saran aja yg nggak mau kelaparan nunggu pesenan datang, sebaiknya reservasi dulu. Waktu kami datang sebenarnya sepi dibanding tempat makan lain disekitarnya. Sengaja memilih ke sini karena sepi. Tapi mgkn juga manajemennya yg kurang bagus itu yg menyebabkan sepi. review_translated_text: Came here for an impromptu family breaking fast. I swear the management is not good. When the fasting month is anticipated, something should be provided to break the fast and prepared beforehand at least a drink. Several tables were given pudding and mineral water, but our empty table was not given anything until half past 7 before the drinks arrived. It also reminded us back and forth that our table didnt have any drinks at all. Just a suggestion for those who dont want to go hungry waiting for their order to arrive, its best to make a reservation first. When we arrived it was actually quiet compared to other places to eat nearby. I deliberately chose here because it was quiet. But its also possible that poor management is what causes it to be quiet. The place and facilities are actually good, there is a prayer room, toilets, a large area so children can play freely. The taste of the food is standard, the menu choices are many and varied. Hopefully the owner can further develop and improve his service which tends to take a long time and lack of preparation.

Overall, I had a delightful experience at this restaurant. The atmosphere was lovely, the prices were reasonable, and the food was flavorful. However, I would have appreciated more vegetarian options on the menu. The cocktails were particularly enjoyable! The service was excellent until they directly asked for tips, which I found a bit amusing. In Spanish culture, tipping is typically voluntary, and it felt odd to be asked directly. As this is a Spanish restaurant, I expected them to be more attuned to cultural norms. Nonetheless, everything else was fabulous!

review_translated_text: Cafe in Tirtodipuran that cant be seen whether its busy or from outside... Indoor with AC... the thing that makes you confused is the choice of table... for the crowded (large) wooden table... its aesthetic but not comfortable for working on a laptop... The small one is good for solo but I think its a bit too nice... there are some near the toilet line... For coffee, its good... the mix plater is ok... For 45 thousand & you can get wings and onion rings, its ok... Ample parking at the back...& free again... Its just a shame that when it opens at noon (11 oclock) WLP says its going forward to 10 oclock... yes, you still have to wait for 10 oclock first... Parking: Spacious in the back... join the showroom parking & kayak, there is some kind of accommodation in the back too

The taste is also right on the tongue, with a mainstay menu of coffee and other drinks. A fairly large and paid parking lot is provided. Wheelchair access is also provided by a ramp and there is a corridor from the parking lot to the cafe. Can bring children because the place is quite spacious Vegetarian options: Salads are available as an alternative food for vegetable lovers and those on a diet Dietary restrictions: Salads are available as an alternative food for vegetable lovers and those on a diet Parking: A fairly large and paid parking lot is provided. review_text: Terletak di Pengasih, Kulon Progo, tempat makan ini menawarkan perpaduan konsep pedesaan dan modern. Menawarkan pemandangan bentangan sungai yang menarik dan instagramable. Fasilitasnya lengkap, area parkir luas, toilet, mushola, tempat cuci tangan, tempatnya bersih, dan area makan dengan meja kursi atau lesehan. Variasi pilihan menu yang merakyat dan mudah diterima lidah, seperti garang asem, pepes, olahan ayam/bebek/ikan . Pilihan minuman juga tak kalah beragam, termasuk minuman sejuta umat...kopi. review_translated_text: Located in Pengasih, Kulon Progo, this eating place offers a combination of rustic and modern concepts. Offers an interesting and instagrammable view of the river stretch. The facilities are complete, large parking area, toilets, prayer room, hand washing place, clean place, and dining area with tables and chairs. A variety of menu choices that are popular and easily accepted by the tongue, such as garang asem, pepes, processed chicken/duck/fish. The choice of drinks is no less diverse, including the drink of a million people...coffee. In terms of taste, its not bad and the price is standard, affordable. Because some of the outdoor dining areas provide quite a lot of sunlight during the day.

review_text: Tempat nongki di dekat jantung kota Wates yg sering rame, banyak pelajar atau mahasiswa yg nongki2 sambil ngerjain tugas di sini. Vibes nya cocok banget untuk ngobrol atau nyari insipirasi nugas. Ada dua pilihan tempat duduk, non smoking dan smoking area. Karena bawa bocil, tentu memilih yg non smoking area. Ada baby chair yg amat membantu ortu yg tetap ingin bisa makan tenang tapi jg tetap bs mengawasi anak. Dine in di sini waktu bulan ramadhan. Pelayan nya memberi tahu bahwa ada free infused Water dan buah potong. Boleh refill air minum dingin ataupun hangat. Kalo yg hangat bisa menghubungi pelayan. Mushola nya bersih dan nyaman karena alat solat nya wangi. Ditambah pula ada kipas angin di dalam mushola jd mengurangi rasa gerah. Makanannya ada yg berat dan ada camilan. Pesan 3 makanan berat (chicken curry, blackpepper, dan teriyaki) semuanya enak dan mengenyangkan sekali. Ada jg donat plus croissant yg enak. Minuman nya pesan 2 coffee dan 1 non coffee. Bisa lebih murah ketika menggunakan member. Overall, tempat oke, makanan minuman okee, dan pelayan yg amat ramah+informatif Kid-friendliness: Ada baby chair nya
review_translated_text: A hangout place near the heart of Wates city which is often busy, lots of students hang out while doing assignments here. The vibe is really suitable for chatting or looking for task inspiration. There are two seating options, non-smoking and smoking areas. Because you brought small bottles, of course you chose a non-smoking area. There are baby chairs which are very helpful for parents who still want to be able to eat in peace but also be able to supervise their children. Dine in here during Ramadan. The waiter told him that there was free infused water and cut fruit. You can refill cold or warm drinking water. If its warm, you can contact the waiter. The prayer room is clean and comfortable because the prayer tools smell good. Plus there is a fan in the prayer room to reduce the feeling of stifling heat. There are heavy meals and snacks. Order 3 heavy dishes (chicken curry, blackpepper and teriyaki) all of which are delicious and very filling. There are also delicious donuts and croissants. Drinks ordered 2 coffee and 1 non-coffee. It can be cheaper when using members. Overall, the place is okay, the food and drinks are okay, and the waiters are very friendly + informative Kid-friendliness: Theres a baby chair

review_text: Judulnya pecel lele, tapi menu lauk disini lumayan komplit. Ada lele, nila, cakalang, ayam kampung, ayam kota, tahu, tempe, jamur, terong dan lain-lain. Rasa ayam gorengnya cenderung agak manis, sambel terasinya sedang, tidak terlalu pedas. Untuk yang hobi pedas bisa pilih sambel bawang. Menu favorit kalo kesini cakalang bakar, bumbunya meresap dan ikannya empuk, enak. Porsi nasinya banyak, dijamin kenyang. Sambel dan lalapan juga cukup banyak. Menu sayurnya memang kurang komplit, paling ca atau tumis kangkung atau jamur tiram. Minuman tersedia beberapa pilihan, ada jus juga. Selain nasi, lauk dan sayur, disini juga bisa beli kebab. Area makan cukup luas, area parkir motor memadai. Untuk parkir mobil bisa di seberang warung.
review_translated_text: The title is catfish pecel, but the side dish menu here is quite complete. There are catfish, tilapia, skipjack, free-range chicken, city chicken, tofu, tempeh, mushrooms, eggplant and others. The taste of the fried chicken tends to be a bit sweet, the chili paste is medium, not too spicy. For those who like spicy food, you can choose onion chili sauce. The favorite menu here is grilled skipjack tuna, the spices penetrate and the fish is tender, delicious. The portion of rice is large, guaranteed to fill you up. There are also quite a lot of sambal and fresh vegetables. The vegetable menu is not complete, at most ca or stir-fried kale or oyster mushrooms. Several choices of drinks are available, there are juices too. Apart from rice, side dishes and vegetables, you can also buy kebabs here. The dining area is quite spacious, the motorbike parking area is adequate. You can park your car across from the shop.

review_text: Restoran bernuansa Jawa yang terletak tidak jauh dari Bandara Yogyakarta International Airport (YIA) Kulon Progo, memberikan suguhan pemandangan sawah.  Pengunjung biasanya sambil nunggu pesawat, datangbke resto ini untuk menyantap kuliner ndeso sembari menikmati momen terbenamnya mentari. Jolotundo terletak di area persawahan wilayah Kalurahan Sogan, Kapanewon Wates, Kulon Progo. Lokasinya tergolong dekat dengan bandara YIA, yakni berkisar 8,7 km atau 15 menit perjalanan menggunakan kendaraan bermotor.  Tempat kuliner ini mengusung konsep tradisional Jawa. Bisa dilihat dari struktur bangunan yang menggunakan joglo khas Jogja komplit dengan ornamen pendukungnya.  Resto ini menyediakan hidangan tradisional atau yang beken disebut menu ndeso. Menu andalannya yakni sayur lodeh, tempe lombok hijau, tumis kikil, ayam bumbu lengkuas dan oseng daun pepaya. Sembari menyantap hidangan ndeso, pengunjung bisa menikmati pemandangan alam sekitar berupa hamparan sawah. Jika datang saat sore hari, pengunjung dapat menyaksikan momen terbenamnya matahari yang tampak jelas dari tempat ini. Resto ini menyediakan fasilitas lain berupa keliling pedesaan mengucapkan mobil Jeep. Cukup merogoh kocek Rp50 ribu per orang, pengunjung bisa jalan-jalan santai berkeliling desa dan area persawahan sekitar.
review_translated_text: This Javanese restaurant is located not far from Yogyakarta International Airport (YIA) Kulon Progo, offering views of the rice fields. Visitors usually come to this restaurant while waiting for their plane to eat indeso culinary delights while enjoying the sunset. Jolotundo is located in the rice fields of Sogan Village, Kapanewon Wates, Kulon Progo. The location is relatively close to YIA airport, which is around 8.7 km or 15 minutes by motor vehicle. This culinary place carries a traditional Javanese concept. It can be seen from the building structure which uses a typical Joglo joglo complete with supporting ornaments. This restaurant provides traditional dishes or what is popularly known as the ndeso menu. The mainstay menu is vegetable lodeh, green Lombok tempeh, stir-fried kikil, chicken with galangal spices and stir-fried papaya leaves. While eating ndeso dishes, visitors can enjoy the surrounding natural scenery in the form of expanses of rice fields. If you come in the afternoon, visitors can watch the sunset which is clearly visible from this place. This restaurant provides other facilities in the form of traveling around the countryside using a Jeep. Just spend IDR 50 thousand per person, visitors can take a leisurely walk around the village and surrounding rice fields.

review_text: Pertama tama saya ucapkan banyak Terima kasih kepada owner gubug makan iwak kalen Kota Wates ini,perlu diketahui pada review kali ini saya tidak akan mereview makanan,minuman,dan fasilitas yg ada (mushola,parkiran,toilet,dsb),Melainkan pada review ini saya akan membagikan hasil jepretan saya di tempat ini.Tidak banyak tempat makan yang berada di pingger rel dengan view bagus seperti disini,saya sendiri seorang penggemar kereta api dari Surabaya jauh2 datang kesini karena ingin hunting Kereta api disini dengan latar sawah,ketika sy kesana kondisi cuaca agak mendung jadi pencahayaan kurang mendukung (hasil foto sdh sy edit) tapi itu tidak masalah, pastinya jika kondisi cerah hasil foto akan lebih bagus lagi.Jika hunting ka disini saya sarankan dari ayunan/taman kecil di tengah, jika di gubuk yg paling ujung dg lensa yg sy pakai (tamron 70-300mm) belum bisa muat 1 rangkaian kereta di 1 frame (yg mencapai 10-12 kereta) mungkin klo pakai lensa dg fl lebih rendah sepertinya muat di 1 frame, namun jika itu ka bandara/prameks atau ka yg pendek cukup di 1 frame, untuk hasil lebih lanjut bisa cek di ig saya @di.to_86 (foto-foto akan sy upload Q1 2024).Sekali lagi saya mengucapkan banyak Terima kasih kepada owner tempat ini yg sudah berhasil Memanfaatkan lokasi dengan daya tarik makan sambil liat kereta lewat sekaligus memberikan kita para pecinta kereta api utk opsi hunting yg juga menarik di kawasan kulon progo. Parking: Parkir luas cocok utk rombongan Kid-friendliness: Sangat sesuai utk anak-anak karena bisa makan sambil liat kereta api lewat Wheelchair accessibility: utk kursi roda sedikit kurang ramah dikarenakan tempatnya yg tidak rata dan sedikit ada tangga2 kecil.
review_translated_text: First of all, I would like to say a big thank you to the owner of the iwak kalen food hut in Wates City. Please note that in this review I will not review the food, drinks and existing facilities (mosque, parking, toilets, etc.), but in this review I will I will share the results of my shots at this place. There are not many places to eat on the edge of the railroad with a good view like here. I myself am a train fan from Surabaya who came all the way here because I wanted to hunt trains here with a backdrop of rice fields, when I went there The weather conditions were a bit cloudy so the lighting wasnt very favorable (I have edited the photos) but thats not a problem, of course if the conditions are sunny the photos will be even better. If youre hunting here, I recommend from the swing/small garden in the middle, if youre in the hut, the best The end with the lens I use (Tamron 70-300mm) cant fit 1 series of trains in 1 frame (which reaches 10-12 trains) maybe if you use a lens with a lower fl it seems like it can fit in 1 frame, but if its for an airport/premex Or for short ones, just 1 frame, for further results, you can check my IG @di.to_86 (I will upload the photos in Q1 2024). Once again I say a big thank you to the owner of this place who has successfully utilized it. A location with the attraction of eating while watching the trains pass by also gives us train lovers an interesting hunting option in the Kulon Progo area. Parking: Ample parking suitable for groups Kid-friendliness: Very suitable for children because they can eat while watching the trains go by Wheelchair accessibility: Its a little less friendly for wheelchairs because the place is uneven and there are a few small steps.

review_translated_text: The place is strategic, the natural view is really good, there is a green view to the west, the atmosphere is aesthetic, the area is large, there is parking, a prayer room, a restroom, and many choices of places to choose from, I went there twice for meetings, its good

review_text: kesini pas weekday dan baru aja buka jadi masih sepi tempatnya, makanan overall enak apalagi dengan harga yang sangat terjangkau (10k-30k an). tempatnya ga terlalu luas tapi tertata rapi, bersih dan pemandangan yg asri, sangat nyaman buat nongkrong santai nikmati angin sepoi . worth it Parking: tempat parkir nya disebelah cafe, bisa untuk motor dan mobil.
review_translated_text: I came here on a weekday and it had just opened so the place was still quiet, overall the food was delicious especially at very affordable prices (10k-30k). The place is not too big but it is neatly arranged, clean and has beautiful views, very comfortable for hanging out and enjoying the breeze. worth it Parking: The parking lot is next to the cafe, suitable for motorbikes and cars.

review_translated_text: There are quite a lot of seats, parking is available but not large enough, the waiter doesnt take too long, there is a prayer room, the view is also beautiful

review_text: Pesan sup iga, Snack platter, iga bakar dan 3 minuman. Pesan dari jam 5 sore dengan harapan pas buka puasa hidangan sudah tersaji. Yg pertama disajikan sup iga, nunggu 10 menit baru minuman disajikan, 15 menit kemudian Snack platter disajikan ( sup iga lumayan enak). Sampe suami selesai makan,  pesananku iga bakar belum juga disajikan. Sampe nanya 3x ke pegawainya dijawab masih disiapkan. Pas datang... Taraaaaa iga bakar dan nasi dalam keadaan dingin dan daging alot. Laahhh berarti sebenarnya udah dimasak dari tadi donk?
review_translated_text: Order rib soup, snack platter, grilled ribs and 3 drinks. Order from 5 pm with the hope that by the time you break the fast the dish will be served. The first one was served rib soup, waited 10 minutes before drinks were served, 15 minutes later the snack platter was served (rib soup was quite delicious). Until my husband finished eating, my order of grilled ribs had not yet been served. When I asked the staff 3 times, they answered it was still being prepared. When it arrived... Taraaaaa the grilled ribs and rice were cold and the meat was tough. Laahhh, does that mean its actually been cooked before?

Pelayanannya juga oke, harga ramah dikantong.. Dan rasanya juga enak..  .. Saya kesana jam 9an.. The service is also good, the prices are pocket friendly... And it tastes delicious too..  .. I went there at 9 oclock.. The weather is a bit hot, maybe its even better in the afternoon so its not too hot and you can see the evening sky...

review_text: Sengaja kesini karena emg nyari tempat makan dengan view yg sejuk dipandang, angin sepoi sepoi dan bisa menikmati hidangan dengan tenang.. so far, tidak ada yg mengecewakan untuk makan, minum dan snack nya.. terima kasih

review_text: Went to had lunch hoping their meals will be as great as the Bale Raos just to see its not (sorry to say). But again, it was a good experience for me.

German tourists (couple): Delicious food, a bit too spicy for my palate. Vegetarian alternatives upon request. Long wait for the food (40 minutes). Great ambience and mini tour of the Sultans brothers premises. Vegetarian options: Simply state that you want vegetarian food, then swap the meat side dish for tofu or other soy dishes.
review_translated_text: Deutsche Touristen (Ehepaar): Leckeres Essen, fur meinen Gaumen etwas zu scharf. Auf Wunsch vegetarische Alternativen. Lange Wartezeit auf das Essen (40 Min.). Tolles Ambiente und Mini-Fuhrung durch die Raumlichkeiten des Bruders des Sultans. Vegetarian options: einfach angeben, dass vegetarisch gewunscht ist, dann tauschen sie die Fleischbeilage in Tofu oder andere Sojagerichte.

review_text: Menikmati makanan dengan suasana keraton, berasa jadi sultan semalem. Hahahaa

review_text: Terrific food, terrific service, great environment. Having tried the restaurant linked to the palace, I thought this was tastier, with better ventilation and  no flies! Gentle gamelan music in the air, birdsong from burung kuku and other songbirds and the gentle December breeze made it really pleasant. I enjoyed my orange juice, with fresh lime accents! It was so good I had to go for seconds and then the nasi kuning was super tasty with impeccably made side dishes. Each one bursting with flavor and a good complement for the meal. Loved it! We also got their version of coconut rice, and a super yummy braised beef short rib with fried rice! Not to mention to super fresh and tasty tahu telur. Mmm

review_text: Datang sudah malam sekitar jam 18:30 kalo di map tutup jam 17:00. Pas Dateng ternyata masih buka. Kalo malam sudah sepi suasananya, tapi kalo waktunya luang agak mending sih jadi bisa santai di sini. Diiringi Gending Jawa jadi makin syahdu. Kunjungan 1 Sept 2023
review_translated_text: Arriving late at around 18:30, if on the map it closes at 17:00. When I arrived, it turned out it was still open. review_text: This opulent place is actually still a royal residence. Serving menu available for the royal. Not overly price, especially considering the location and the atmosphere. Open for bfast until 17:00 - its a residence, so closed in the evening. Highly recommended.

review_text: Setelah mampir ke mari jadi gak penasaran lagi bagaimana isi dalam rumah bangsawan Jogja. Makanannya yang dihidangkan pun lezat dan kebanyakan mulai jarang ditemukan di tempat lain.
review_translated_text: After stopping by here, Im no longer curious about whats inside the Jogja noble house. The food served is delicious and most of it is rarely found elsewhere.

review_text: Resto ini sepertinya usaha keluarga. Tempatnya pun merupakan rumah keluarga Gusti Joyokusumo (adik kandung Sri Sultan HB X). Berkunjung ke sini saat malam hari, dan bertepatan menghadiri HUT salah satu OKP di Jogja. Makanan yang disajikan enak. Pelayanan ramah. Suasana di sini sangat kental dengan kebudayaan Jawa baik itu bangunan, kuliner, cerita, benda peninggalan, hingga terdengar alunan gamelan khas Jogja. Terdapat banyak foto di dinding yang berisi foto keluarga Gusti Joyo, HB X, dan bahkan keluarga keraton lainnya. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.
review_translated_text: This restaurant seems to be a family business. The place is also the family home of Gusti Joyokusumo (the younger brother of Sri Sultan HB Visited here at night, and coincided with attending the anniversary of one of the OKPs in Jogja. The food served is delicious. Friendly service. The atmosphere here is very thick with Javanese culture, including buildings, culinary delights, stories, heritage objects, and even the sounds of typical Jogja gamelan. There are many photos on the walls containing photos of the Gusti Joyo family, HB X, and even other palace families. Was a nice experience in Gadri Resto.

review_text: Perched atop the ibis Styles Yogyakarta, D  Skybar offers a breathtaking panoramic view of the cityscape, making it the perfect spot for a memorable evening out. As I ascended to the rooftop venue, I was immediately captivated by the vibrant ambiance and stylish decor, setting the stage for an unforgettable experience. Once seated, I couldn t help but marvel at the sweeping vistas of Yogyakarta spread out before me. The skyline glowed with the warm hues of sunset, casting a magical spell over the bustling city below. It was the ideal backdrop for savoring a refreshing cocktail and soaking in the lively atmosphere. Speaking of cocktails, D  Skybar boasts an extensive menu of handcrafted drinks, each concoction expertly crafted to perfection. From classic favorites to innovative twists, there was something to suit every palate. I opted for their signature Skytini, a delightful blend of tropical flavors that perfectly complemented the balmy evening air. While the drinks were undoubtedly the star of the show, D  Skybar also offers a tempting selection of small bites and appetizers to accompany your libations. From crispy calamari to savory sliders, each dish was expertly prepared and bursting with flavor, adding an extra layer of indulgence to the experience. One aspect that truly stood out to me was the impeccable service provided by the attentive staff. Despite the bustling atmosphere, the staff remained attentive and personable, ensuring that every guest felt welcomed and well taken care of throughout the evening. Overall, my experience at D  Skybar @ ibis Styles Yogyakarta was nothing short of spectacular. Whether you re looking for a romantic date night spot or a chic venue to unwind with friends, D  Skybar offers an unparalleled experience that is sure to leave a lasting impression.

review_text: Went there around 1pm and no-one was at the bar. Waited around a while and had to go downstairs to the hotel reception to ask them if the rooftop restaurant was open (it was) and for them to send someone up to provide a menu and take our order. Once the waiter had arrived though, service was very good. Food was pretty decent and it was nice having a rooftop view of the Yogakarta town. Mushroom soup was yummy, but its a small dish so definitely consider it a side dish and not a main. Spring rolls were great as well - Id recommend that as a good side dish too. Going here for lunch was actually very good since it was very quiet - this seems to be a popular evening place as well if you want night time busy vibes instead though. The only reason I put this at 4 star is because no-one is actually attending the bar once it opens for lunch and I had to prompt reception to send someone up.

review_text: Poffen Cafe memikat pengunjung dengan desain interior yang indah dan aesthetic. Dekorasi yang dipilih dengan cermat menciptakan atmosfer yang menenangkan dan Instagramable. Pilihan furnitur yang stylish dan perpaduan warna yang baik membuat pengalaman bersantai di cafe ini menjadi lebih menyenangkan. Kelebihan Poffen Cafe terletak pada ruang yang luas, mencakup area indoor, outdoor, dan rooftop. Area indoor memberikan kenyamanan dan suasana yang hangat, sementara area outdoor dan rooftop memberikan pengunjung opsi untuk menikmati suasana segar dan pemandangan sekitar. Ini memberikan pengalaman bersantai yang fleksibel. Poffen Cafe tidak hanya unggul dalam kopi, tetapi juga menyajikan menu kue yang lezat. Pilihan variasi kue yang enak memberikan opsi bagi pengunjung yang ingin menikmati camilan yang manis dan memuaskan. Kualitas bahan dan rasa yang khas dapat membuat pengunjung ingin kembali mencoba berbagai kue. Tentu saja, sebagai coffee shop, kualitas kopi di Poffen Cafe harus dipuji. Kopi yang disajikan memiliki cita rasa yang konsisten, mencerminkan perhatian terhadap kualitas biji kopi dan proses penyeduhan yang baik. Varian menu kopi yang beragam memuaskan selera pengunjung pecinta kopi. Jadi, Poffen Cafe adalah destinasi yang sempurna bagi pecinta kopi dan mereka yang menghargai suasana indah. Dengan kombinasi interior yang aesthetic, ruang yang luas, menu kue yang lezat, dan pilihan rooftop yang menarik, Poffen Cafe dapat menjadi tempat yang sangat menikmati bagi mereka yang mencari pengalaman bersantai dan menikmati kopi di tengah atmosfer yang menyenangkan.
review_translated_text: Poffen Cafe attracts visitors with its beautiful and aesthetic interior design. Carefully selected decorations create a calming and Instagrammable atmosphere. The choice of stylish furniture and a good combination of colors makes the experience of relaxing at this cafe more enjoyable. The advantage of Poffen Cafe lies in its spacious space, including indoor, outdoor and rooftop areas. The indoor area provides comfort and a warm atmosphere, while the outdoor and rooftop areas give visitors the option to enjoy the fresh atmosphere and surrounding views. This provides a flexible relaxing experience. Poffen Cafe not only excels in coffee, but also serves a delicious cake menu. A delicious selection of cake variations provides options for diners who want to enjoy a sweet and satisfying snack. The quality of the ingredients and distinctive taste can make visitors want to try various cakes again. Of course, as a coffee shop, the quality of the coffee at Poffen Cafe must be praised. The coffee served has a consistent taste, reflecting attention to the quality of the coffee beans and a good brewing process. A wide variety of coffee menus satisfy the tastes of coffee lovers. So, Poffen Cafe is the perfect destination for coffee lovers and those who appreciate a beautiful atmosphere. With a combination of aesthetic interior, spacious space, delicious cake menu, and attractive rooftop options, Poffen Cafe can be a really enjoyable place for those looking for the experience of relaxing and enjoying coffee amidst a pleasant atmosphere.

review_text: Such a nice place and a nice owner

The meals are simple and delicious, and the interior decoration is also cute. You can feel the owners personal ingenuity  I got sunburned when I was in Yogyakarta, and it was not easy to find aloe vera in the local store. After asking the owner, he cut several pieces from the garden directly for me. My friends and I    we felt well taken care of, these kind and warm locals are one of the lovely memories in Yogyakarta

Great local breakfast!! The boss was very friendly and efficient and I was able to get everything I was looking for at a more than fair price! You can find both savory and sweet options: pressed fruit juices, spiced teas (local drink in Yogyakarta), excellent +++ fruit-filled pancakes, fruit-yogurt-granola bowls, as well as savory dishes from same kind as those found almost everywhere: nasi goreng, noodles etc. Each item costs around 25,000 rp, so with a hearty breakfast you can easily get by for 100,000 rp As a bonus, the room where we eat is rather pretty: wooded, surrounded by a garden imitating a small jungle and in a small street therefore quite quiet, and filled with paintings that the owner paints himself, which is everything also in the atmosphere of Yogyakarta, the  artist city of Indonesia
review_translated_text: Super petit-dejeuner local !! Le patron etait tres sympa et efficace et jai pu avoir tout ce que je cherchais a un prix plus que correct ! Vous pourrez trouver du sale comme du sucre : des jus de fruits presses, des thes aux epices (boisson locale a Yogyakarta), des crepes fourrees aux fruits excellentes +++, des bowls fruit-yaourt-granola, ainsi que des plats sales du meme genre que ceux quon trouve un peu partout : nasi goreng, nouilles etc. Chaque article coute environ 25000 rp, ce qui fait quavec un copieux petit dejeuner on peut sen sortir facilement pour 100000 rp En prime, la salle ou lon mange est plutot jolie : boisee, entouree dun jardin imitant une petite jungle et dans une petite rue donc assez calme, et remplie de tableaux que le patron peint lui-meme, ce qui est tout a fait dans lambiance de Yogyakarta egalement, la ville dartistes dIndonesie

review_text: Very nice location, fair prices, good service

review_translated_text: If life feels very flat, calm and calm lacks surprises, shop at this shop. There is no price listed on the item, the total is spectacular. Then, because I didnt have anything to do, I just recalculated my shopping on the train at a reasonable price, the total price should only be half, so its okay to give it up to 70  because its a special place to rent. Tugu Station, like that. The place where I separated to return to an LDR with an ex who was still dating. Previously, you could carry it to the train, now its a different story. The cashier wasnt friendly, it could be that he had that attitude or there was a problem, he didnt really understand. The merchandise I bought was dusty, maybe it meant it was good for tayammum but I didnt pray :( Two weeks passed, this afternoon I was packing up my bags and found a shopping receipt at this shop, then realized the plastic bag was worth 2000:((

review_text: B Coffee terletak di Jogokaryan, Yogyakarta menonjolkan suasana kafe yang unik dan aestetik, berlokasi dalam kompleks Hotel Burza, menjadikannya destinasi kuliner yang menarik di Yogyakarta. Kelebihan yang dapat diapresiasi adalah amenitas pelengkap seperti kamar mandi dan lahan parkir yang luas, memberikan nilai tambah pada pengalaman pengunjung. Meskipun ruangannya tidak dilengkapi dengan AC, namun sirkulasi udara dan pencahayaan yang baik menjadikannya tempat yang nyaman untuk diskusi dan bersantai. Satu-satunya kekurangan tampaknya terletak pada akses untuk lansia dan pengguna kursi roda, yang mungkin menjadi pertimbangan untuk perbaikan dalam meningkatkan aksesibilitas. Dengan demikian, B Coffee bisa lebih menonjolkan konsepnya sebagai tempat bersantai yang nyaman dan menarik, dengan peningkatan kecil pada aksesibilitas yang akan menjadikannya lebih ramah bagi semua pengunjung. Hal ini menjadi pertimbangan saran konstruktif untuk mempertimbangkan peningkatan pada desain dan aksesibilitas kafe. Vegetarian options: Tidak ada menu khusus bagi para pengunjung vegetarian Dietary restrictions: Tidak ada menu khusus bagi para pengunjung yang sedang diet makanan Parking: Terdapat valet parking dan parkir luas namun berbayar Kid-friendliness: Bisa dijadikan pilihan wisata bagi anak anak Wheelchair accessibility: Tidak tersedia kursi roda maupun akses bagi pengunjung distabilitas
review_translated_text: B Coffee is located in Jogokaryan, Yogyakarta, featuring a unique and aesthetic cafe atmosphere, located within the Burza Hotel complex, making it an attractive culinary destination in Yogyakarta. The advantages that can be appreciated are the complementary amenities such as bathrooms and a large parking area, which provide added value to the visitor experience. Even though the room is not equipped with air conditioning, good air circulation and lighting make it a comfortable place for discussions and relaxing. The only drawback appears to be access for the elderly and wheelchair users, which may be a consideration for improvements to improve accessibility. In this way, B Coffee can further emphasize its concept as a comfortable and attractive place to relax, with small improvements in accessibility that will make it more welcoming for all visitors. This is a constructive suggestion to consider improvements to the design and accessibility of the cafe. Vegetarian options: There is no special menu for vegetarian visitors Dietary restrictions: There is no special menu for visitors who are on a diet Parking: There is valet parking and spacious parking but it is paid Kid-friendliness: Can be used as a tourist choice for children Wheelchair accessibility: There are no wheelchairs or access for visitors with disabilities

review_text: Pasar Bintaos adalah pasar Desa, Pasar yang dikelola oleh Pemerintah Desa Sidoharjo ini berada dilokasi yang sangat strategis tepatnya berada di wilayah Paukuhan Bintaos Sidoharjo Tepus Gunungkidul. Untuk umurnya sudah tidak kita ragukan lagi, pasar ini merupakan pasar tertua yang berada di Kecamatan Tepus khususunya di Desa Sidoharjo. Hari pasaran di Pasar Bintaos ini pada Pahing dan Kliwon, dulunya hanya Pahing saja tapi mulai beberapa tahun lalu ditambah lagi dengan hari Kliwon. Walaupun pahing dan kliwon namun setiap malamnya anda juga bisa menikmati wedangan dan berbagai macam makanan khas lokal di pasar ini, karena setiap malam pasti ada yang buka dan menjajakan hidanganya. Teh panas gula batu dan makanan seperti bakwan, tahu, jadah, tempe, pisgor, dll ada juga Sego gendhong (Nasi Bungkus). Lokasi sangat strategis karena berada di pinggir jalan nasional yang juga merupakan jalur wisata pantai. Selamat Menikmati
review_translated_text: Bintaos Market is a village market, this market which is managed by the Sidoharjo Village Government is in a very strategic location, precisely in the Paukuhan Bintaos Sidoharjo Tepus Gunungkidul area. We can no longer doubt its age, this market is the oldest market in Tepus District, especially in Sidoharjo Village. Market days at Bintaos Market are in Pahing and Kliwon, previously it was just Pahing but starting a few years ago Kliwon day was added. Even though its pahing and kliwon, every night you can also enjoy wedangan and various kinds of local specialties at this market, because every night someone is definitely open and selling their dishes. Hot tea with rock sugar and foods such as bakwan, tofu, jadah, tempeh, pisgor, etc. There is also Sego gendhong (wrapped rice). The location is very strategic because it is on the side of the national road which is also the coastal tourist route. Enjoy

review_text: Es campur dan ayam goreng mentega-nya masih enak! Langganan dari jaman aku kecil waktu masih di Jogja. September 2023 nyempetin jajan lagi kesini dan ingin nikmati lagi rasa seru anak jogja tahun 90an ketemu konsep prasmanan. Langsung milih 1. Nasi merah campur nasi putih 2. Ayam goreng mentega. Btw, disajikannya a la sate ya disunduk gitu, makanya unik 3. Kornet goreng 4. Tumis jepan 5. Balado terong 6. Kerupuk udang 7. Es teler durian Yuk madhiang gedhen harga di bawah 50ribu, Yumm! Buat ngiraser yang pengen masakan fusion jadul atau nostalgia, bisa njajal es Eny AM Sangaji, utaranya tugu jogja, depan pop hotel! Note : Setelah lama banget nggak ngiras di es Eny, kesan pertama, sepi banget! 1 jam kami disini baru ada 2 pengunjung baru. Nanya ke mbak-mbak yang jaga, sejak pandemi emang jadi sepi. Restart itu emang ga mudah sih ya. Yang jadi catetan. Sayur kuah-nya dingin dan nggak dipanasi. Mungkin bisa kali taruh di semacam thermos jadi masih anget lah ketika disajikan.
review_translated_text: The mixed ice and butter fried chicken are still delicious! A subscription from when I was little when I was still in Jogja. September 2023, Ill have a snack here again and want to enjoy the exciting taste of Jogja kids from the 90s who meet the buffet concept. Just choose 1. Brown rice mixed with white rice 2. Butter fried chicken. BTW, its served satay style, so its served like that, thats why its unique 3. Fried corned beef 4. Japanese stir fry 5. Eggplant balado 6. Shrimp crackers 7. Durian ice cream Come on, madhiang gedhen, price under 50 thousand, Yumm! For those who want old school or nostalgic fusion cuisine, you can try Eny AM Sangaji ice, north of Tugu Jogja, in front of the Pop Hotel! Note: After a long time without drinking Enys ice, the first impression was, it was really quiet! In the 1 hour we were here there were only 2 new visitors. Ask the ladies on duty, since the pandemic its been quiet. Restarting isnt easy, is it? Which is a note. The vegetable soup is cold and not heated. Maybe you could put it in some kind of thermos so its still warm when served.

review_text: Nestled in a quaint corner of the city, Susu Segar Murni Pak Warto beckons with the promise of wholesome dairy goodness. As I entered the humble establishment, I was greeted by the sight of gleaming stainless-steel tanks brimming with fresh milk, setting the stage for what I hoped would be a delightful dairy experience. The star of the show, undoubtedly, was the fresh milk itself. Sourced directly from local farms, each sip was a testament to the purity and quality of the dairy produced by Pak Warto. Whether enjoyed on its own or incorporated into creamy beverages like milkshakes and lattes, the milk at Susu Segar Murni Pak Warto was nothing short of exceptional. However, while the milk was undoubtedly the highlight of my visit, I couldn t help but notice the modest surroundings of the establishment. The ambiance lacked the sophistication of upscale cafes, but it exuded a charming simplicity that resonated with the authentic farm-to-table experience offered by Pak Warto. With its no-frills approach and focus on quality, Susu Segar Murni Pak Warto epitomizes the essence of pure, unadulterated dairy goodness. In conclusion, my experience at Susu Segar Murni Pak Warto was a delightful journey into the world of fresh dairy. While the ambiance may be modest, the quality of the milk speaks volumes, making it a must-visit destination for dairy enthusiasts and anyone seeking a taste of genuine farm-fresh goodness.

review_text: Tempatnya memiliki vibe santai. Bisa selonjoran tentu saja. Ada bantal-bantal di lantai dua. Baristanya ramah dan baik. Pelayanannya cukup memuaskan. Atmosfer sedikit panas, mengingat masih siang. Ada musik, tapi mungkin terlalu keras saat diputerkannya. Jadi, sedikit menganggu. Tempatnya tidak memiliki bau aneh. Biasa saja. Interiornya gaya-gaya natural retro kayu dan banyak tanaman hijau. Ada komik dan buku yang bisa dipinjam di lantai 1. Makanan pilihannya tergolong sedikit. Makanan yang direkomendasikan adalah indomie kuah susunya. Kentang gorengnya juga renyah. Sejujurnya cukup kecewa dengan masakan yang saya pesan, ayam sambal mantah. Ayamnya kering dan cukup keras. Untungnya diselamatkan dengan sambal mantah dan nasinya (plus sayanya yg belum sarapan). Minuman-minumannya cukup unik dan bervariasi. Saya suka minuman matcha + ice creamnya.  Tempat ini cocok untuk nongki dan makan-makan snacks, kalau mau makan makanan berat mungkin perlu dipertimbangkan terlebih dahulu. Update: ke sini lagi setelah sekian lama. Banyak sekali perubahan, terutama di bagian menu. Sudah banyak tambahan dan varian, terutama ada menu paket ramadhan. Rasanya juga ada perkembangan, setidaknya ayamnya cukup juicy (tidak kering kayak sebelumnya). Ada rak sepatu di bawah (yang sebelumnya nggak ada atau akunya aja yang nggak lihat waktu itu ). Musiknya juga nggak terlalu keras. Vibenya jadi lebih bagus, tenang, dan  nyaman. Anyway, aku salut sih. Terima kasih sudah mau mendengar masukan ulasan.
response_from_owner_text: terimakasih kak ulasannya, sangat membantu, silahkan datang kembali
review_translated_text: The place has a relaxed vibe. You can stretch it out, of course. There are pillows on the second floor. The baristas are friendly and kind. The service is quite satisfying. The atmosphere was a little hot, considering it was still daytime. There is music, but it might be too loud when playing it. So, a little annoying. The place doesnt have any strange smell. Just normal. The interior has a natural retro wood style and lots of green plants. There are comics and books that can be borrowed on the 1st floor. The food choices are quite small. The recommended food is Indomie with milk sauce. The fries are also crispy. To be honest, I was quite disappointed with the dish I ordered, chicken with sambal mantah. The chicken was dry and quite tough. Luckily it was saved by the mantah chili sauce and rice (plus I didnt have breakfast). The drinks are quite unique and varied. I like the matcha drink + ice cream. This place is suitable for hanging out and eating snacks, if you want to eat heavy food you might need to consider it first. Update: here again after a long time. Lots of changes, especially in the menu. There are many additions and variants, especially the Ramadhan package menu. The taste has also improved, at least the chicken is quite juicy (not dry like before). There is a shoe rack below (which wasnt there before or Ill admit I didnt see it at the time ). The music is also not too loud. The vibe is better, calmer and more comfortable. Anyway, I salute you. Thank you for wanting to hear your review input.

review_text: Jujur pertama kali kesini dari Wonosari tuh jaauh bgt, dan waktu sampe jembatan ituu kupikir tempatnya b aja gitu karena gelaap. Sistem penandaan reservator juga unik si ditulisin gitu pake kertas jadi jelas. Aku dapet view yang sejuuk karena deket sungainya, lingkungannya bersih jugaa. Tempatnya nyaman bangeet dan muslim friendly cz ada mushollanya+fasilitas mukena, sarung, sajadah. Sayangnya, buat cuci tangan inii perlu ada sabunnya biar lebih higienis abis makan pake tangan hehe, karena kan modelnya lesehan gitu ya?jadii mau gamau pake tangan dan tangannya bau kecap dst, menurut aku ini perlu banget ada sabun buat sterilisasii & jaga keharuman juga kebersihan tangan. Gitu aja sih buat performa resto dll all the best Hehe maaf ini aku lupaa foto makanan jadii cuma bisa kasij testii foto bareeng temen temen disana. Thank you @RestoBanyuMili udaah jadii tempat ternyaman kamii buaat berbuka puasaa. Parking: Menurutku parkirnya lumayan susah karena motor mobil masii campur gitu, naah tapi semakin lama kita pulangg nantii bakal sepi sendiri & motor kita jadii rapii dibantu tukang parkir hehe. Worth it si menurutku ada tukang parkir yang mau ngerapihin kendaraan, terus juga mau ngebantu kitaa nyebrang. Good facilities
review_translated_text: Honestly, the first time I came here from Wonosari it was really far away, and when I got to the bridge I thought the place was just like that because it was dark. Eeeh, when it arrived it turned out to be really good?!?! I made a reservation the day before, but when I arrived, I just had to eat, no need to wait any longer. The reservation marking system is also unique because it is written on paper so it is clear. I got a cool view because it was near the river, the environment was clean too. The place is really comfortable and Muslim friendly because there is a prayer room + facilities for mukenas, sarongs and prayer mats. Unfortunately, for washing your hands you need to have soap so that its more hygienic after eating with your hands hehe, because thats the way its done on the floor, right? So if you dont want to use your hands and your hands smell like soy sauce etc., in my opinion its really necessary to have soap to sterilize & maintain fragrance and cleanliness. hand. Thats all for restaurant performance etc. all the best Hehe, sorry, I forgot to take photos of the food so I can only test the photos with my friends there. Thank you @RestoBanyuMili for being our most comfortable place to break the fast. Parking: In my opinion, parking is quite difficult because the motorbikes are still mixed up, well, but the longer it takes for us to go home, the more it will be quiet and our motorbikes will be tidy with the help of the parking attendant, hehe. Its worth it, in my opinion, there are parking attendants who want to tidy up the vehicle, and also want to help us cross. Good facilities

review_text: kopi joss adalah minuman kopi khas Yogyakarta yang disajikan bersama arang panas. Arang panas dimasukkan ke dalam seduhan kopi hitam dan gula untuk kemudian dihidangkan. Kopi jos bermula di Angkringan Lek Man, salah satu angkringan yang dianggap legendaris di Yogyakarta. Karena berada di dekat Stasiun Tugu, banyak dari para pelanggan Angkringan Lek Man adalah pegawai perkeretaapian. Para pelanggan ini kebanyakan berasal dari Jawa Timur dan sering memesan kopi kothok, kopi yang jamak di Jawa Timur yang dibuat dengan cara merebus kopi, gula dan air secara bersamaan. Namun kala itu, Lek Man tidak bisa membuat kopi kothok, sehingga Lek Man berinisiatif untuk mencemplungkan arang menyala ke dalam minuman kopi. Dari sana, banyak pelanggan yang suka kopi arang tersebut dan menyebutnya sebagai kopi jos. Kopi jos kemudian banyak ditiru pedagang lain dan menjadi salah satu sajian khas Yogyakarta.
review_translated_text: Joss coffee is a typical Yogyakarta coffee drink served with hot charcoal. Hot charcoal is mixed with black coffee and sugar and then served. Jos coffee started at Angkringan Lek Man, one of the angkringan that is considered legendary in Yogyakarta. Because it is located near Tugu Station, many of Angkringan Lek Mans customers are railway employees. These customers mostly come from East Java and often order kothok coffee, a coffee common in East Java that is made by boiling coffee, sugar and water together. However, at that time, Lek Man couldnt make kothok coffee, so Lek Man took the initiative to plunge burning charcoal into the coffee drink. From there, many customers liked the charcoal coffee and called it jos coffee. Jos coffee was then imitated by many other traders and became one of Yogyakartas typical dishes.

review_text: The internet is faster than some other cafes nearby. The menu are cheapest. Cute cats, cool peeps to hang out with. But not a place for those who enjoy solitude and distance. Good place for those who enjoy or tolerate a little bit of crowd and warmth.

I had high hopes for this place because it had good reviews from people who follow me on Google Maps, but it didnt work for me. The staff occupied the main table in the center of the store, smoking cigarettes while fiddling with their cell phones, and when customers arrived, they returned to their respective posts, and once the service was over, it was time to use their cell phones and smoke again. Even if a cat climbs onto the table and interferes with your meal, instead of chasing it away, you just glance at it. I wasnt going to a friends house, I was paying to go to a cafe, so I didnt feel well. Personally, I will not visit again.

review_translated_text: If you go to Jogja, right in Malioboro, please stop by this bakery. This bakery has been around for decades in Jogja, legendary... dont judge it by the outside appearance, try buying it and taste it... delicious! The latest information, this shop now has a cafe. The drinks offered are still limited to coffee (blended black coffee and spiced milk coffee). Both are worth a try. Ampiran is suitable for taking a short break when walking around Malioboro.

review_text: Salah satu toko roti legendaris di Yogyakarta yang sudah berdiri sejak sebelum Indonesia merdeka. Salah satu produk yang paling terkenal di Toko Roti Djoen ialah ontbijtjoek atau roti gandum hitam. Harganya Rp8.000 per buah ketika saya membeli di sini. Memang agak mahal, sih, untuk sepotong roti. Namun, itu bisa dipahami karena toko ini sudah punya nama besar dan terletak di kawasan yang sangat strategis: Jalan Malioboro. Tokonya bersih dan rapi, menempati sebuah bangunan tua di tepi jalan. Pelayanan bagus dan karyawannya ramah. Cocok untuk jadi tempat berburu buah tangan kalau harga tidak jadi masalah.
review_translated_text: One of the legendary bakeries in Yogyakarta which has been around since before Indonesias independence. One of the most famous products at Toko Roti Djoen is ontbijtjoek or rye bread. The price was IDR 8,000 per piece when I bought it here. Its a bit expensive, though, for a piece of bread. However, this is understandable because this shop already has a big name and is located in a very strategic area: Jalan Malioboro. The shop is clean and neat, occupies an old building on the side of the road. Good service and friendly employees. Suitable as a place to hunt for souvenirs if price is not an issue.

The bread is soft, the nastar cake is too, but theres not too much filling. For ginger lovers, try the ginger cake, its really strong Unfortunately I couldnt try the eclairs and other cakes because I came on Sunday and my father said to make it on weekdays only. review_text: Jogja dan kenangan, katanya seperti itu. Ada yg punya memorabilia sama tempat ini? Masuk ke sini itu spti kembali ke masa lalu tanpa perlu mesin waktu. Bangunan toko dan interiornya khas toko lawasan. Toko roti legendaris, produknya dikemas sederhana, tapi soal rasa boleh diadu. Aneka roti dg resep kuno masih punya pelanggan setia ditengah gempuran produk bakery yg beraneka ragam. Mau roti manis/gurih ada, tinggal pilih. Rasa roti spiku dan semacam nastarnya enak, manis gurih dan wangi. Harganya sangat terjangkau . Lokasi toko berada di dekat pecinan sekitar Ketandan, Malioboro, tak jauh dari tugu pecinan. Konon katanya, produk di sini itu unggul karna tidak pakai pengembang/pengawet, jadi secara tekstur beberapa rotinya agak bikin ekstra usaha buat ngunyahnya
review_translated_text: Jogja and memories, he said like that. Does anyone have memorabilia about this place? Entering here is like going back in time without needing a time machine. The shop building and interior are typical of an old shop. Legendary bakery, the products are packaged simply, but the taste is fine. Various breads with ancient recipes still have loyal customers amidst the onslaught of diverse bakery products. If you want sweet/savory bread, just choose. The taste of spiku bread and a kind of nastar is delicious, sweet, savory and fragrant. The price is very affordable. The location of the shop is near Chinatown around Ketandan, Malioboro, not far from the Chinatown monument. It is said that the product here is superior because it doesnt use leaveners/preservatives, so the texture of some of the bread makes it a little extra effort to chew.

review_text: Saat ke Jogya saya sempatkan mampir ke toko roti legendaris ini stlh sebelumnya sempat bimbang, krn waktu terbatas, antara ke toko roti modern atau legendaris ( di Jakarta bakery modern banyak ). Saya beli roti pisang coklat, kue ontbitjkoek, sus keju, sus isi daging ( krn yg isi vla yg memang favorit disini sdh habis ), amandel kacang tanah. Kue sus keju ternyata di dalamnya berisi potongan keju sementara yg daging berisi olahan daging spt kornet. Kulit sus nya enak sekali. Kombinasi mentega & telur yg digunakan membuat kulit sus ini paling enak diantara sus yg pernah saya beli tmsk dibanding bakery2 se tipe yg ada di Jakarta. Terbayang pasti sus vla nya enak. Ontbijtkoek nya cukup enak, no. 2 terenak setelah bakery legendaris langganan saya yg ada di Jakarta. Roti pisang coklatnya standard tapi pisang nya manis. Toko ini bukanya jam 11 shg agak repot juga menyediakan waktu kesini ditengah tujuan liburan ke Jogya ialah mengunjungi obyek2 wisata yg ada. Lokasinya di Jl. Malioboro sederet dengan pasar Bringharjo.
review_translated_text: When I went to Jogya, I had the chance to stop by this legendary bakery after previously being confused, because time was limited, between going to a modern or legendary bakery (in Jakarta there are lots of modern bakeries). I bought chocolate banana bread, ontbitjkoek cake, cheese eclairs, meat-filled eclairs (because the one filled with vla which is a favorite here has run out), peanut tonsils. It turns out that the cheese eclairs contain pieces of cheese while the meat ones contain processed meat such as corned beef. The eclair skin is really delicious. The combination of butter & eggs used makes this eclair the tastiest among the eclairs Ive ever bought, compared to other types of bakeries in Jakarta. I imagine the sus vla must be delicious. The ontbijtkoek is quite delicious, no. 2nd tastiest after the legendary bakery I frequent in Jakarta. The chocolate banana bread is standard but the banana is sweet. This shop opens at 11 oclock so its a bit of a hassle to find time to come here because the aim of your holiday in Jogya is to visit the existing tourist attractions. The location is on Jl. Malioboro is in a row with Bringharjo market.

review_text: Roti nya enak
review_translated_text: The bread is delicious

review_text: Toko Djoen since 1935. Toko roti legendaris Jogja. Kalau suka roti-roti jadul, bisa cobain ini. Enak dan harganya murah-murah. Roti tawar yang paling gede harganya cuma 20 ribu. Kalau mau fresh bread, bisa datang hari Senin, Kamis, dan Sabtu. Mereka baking di hari itu. Datang jam 1 atau 2 gitu masih kebagian roti yang anget-anget. Di sini ada roti-roti kecil, roti buaya, onbitjkoek (favoritku), kue sus, dan pastri juga. Kue susnya gede, ada isi daging, ada isi keju. Yang pastri ada isi pisang (favoritku) dan ayam. Untuk roti kecil2 lainnya ada rasa cokelat, nanas, kelapa (favoritku), pisang, kacang merah, kacang tanah, roti amandel, dll. Lokasinya di jl Malioboro, deket gerbang Ketandan, seberangnya Ramai Mall, sederetan sama Ramayana Mall. Parkirnya bisa di samping Ramayana. Yang ngelayanin Oma Pin langsung (generasi ke-2), usianya 87 tahun. Oma Pin dibantuin sama anak perempuannya juga sehari-harinya. Mereka manggang rotinya masih pakai oven yang jadul banget itu. Oven chamber segede kamar kos kayak tempat pemanggangan pizza gitu. Nyalainnya pakai solar. Nah, berhubung solar sekarang mahal dan susah nyarinya, itu jadi kendala di mereka juga. Kalau ke sini dilarisin ya gais, biar toko rotinya long last, soalnya legendaris banget nih. Nggak rela kalau sampai tutup
review_translated_text: Toko Djoen since 1935. Jogjas legendary bakery. If you like old school bread, you can try this. Its delicious and the price is cheap. The biggest plain bread only costs 20 thousand. If you want fresh bread, you can come Monday, Thursday and Saturday. They were baking that day. When we arrived at 1 or 2 oclock we still had some really hot bread. Here there are small breads, crocodile bread, onbitjkoek (my favorite), eclairs, and pastries too. The eclairs are big, have meat filling and cheese filling. The pastry contains banana (my favorite) and chicken. For other small breads, there are flavors of chocolate, pineapple, coconut (my favorite), banana, red bean, peanut, tonsil bread, etc. The location is on Jl Malioboro, near the Ketandan gate, opposite Ramai Mall, in the same row as Ramayana Mall. Parking can be next to Ramayana. The one who serves Oma Pin directly (2nd generation), she is 87 years old. Grandma Pin is also helped by her daughter on a daily basis. They still bake the bread using that really old school oven. The oven chamber is as big as a boarding room, like a pizza oven. Turn it on using diesel. Well, since diesel fuel is now expensive and hard to find, thats a problem for them too. If you come here, its a hit, guys, so the bakery shop has long last, because its really legendary. Harga under 15k/pcs buat yg roti satuannya. Isinya cukup banyak, terasa resep kunonya (wangi buttery kenceng, teksturnya bukan yg lembut banget kayak dikasih pelembut tapi). Kusuka yang isi cokelat karena isi cokelatnya yg berasa krenyes-krenyes (?) bukan selai kayak biasanya gitu.
review_translated_text: The location is at the left shop on Jalan Malioboro, before the Ketandan Chinatown gate. An ancient bakery with classic bread choices (chocolate, cheese, meat, jam, plain, etc.). Price under 15k/pcs for individual bread. Theres quite a lot of content, it feels like an old recipe (the strong buttery smell, the texture isnt really soft like if you had softened it). I like the chocolate filled ones because the chocolate filling tastes crunchy (?) instead of jam like usual.

review_text: Bakery legend di jogja, sejak th 30an. Jenis rotinya jadul spt oenbijtkoek, soes, roti buaya, roti pisang dll. Paling suka dgn soes isi pisang-coklat ato isi ragout. Kue2  biasanya matang mulai jam 13.00-15.00,  masih hangat, roti tawarnya tebal gendut utuh belum dipotong, minta sekalian dipotong jg bisa. Dulu th 80an, donatnya empuk tebal, tp skrg sepertinya sdh tdk bikin lg. Parkir mbl bs di area parkir ketandan yg luas, masuk dr ramayana, jalan kaki 150m bs sambil sekalian eksplore kampung pecinan ketandan
review_translated_text: Bakery legend in Jogja, since the 30s. The types of bread are old school like oenbijtkoek, soes, crocodile bread, banana bread etc. Most like it with banana-chocolate sauce or ragout filling. The cakes are usually cooked from 13.00-15.00, still warm, the white bread is thick, fat, whole and hasnt been cut, you can ask to cut it at the same time. Back in the 80s, the donuts were thick and soft, but now it seems they dont make them anymore. You can park in the large Ketandan parking area, enter from the Ramayana, walk 150m and explore Ketandan Chinatown at the same time

review_text: Toko roti legendaris di Malioboro. Sudah melapak semenjak masa kolonial, Toko Djoen kondang akan roti pisangnya yg inuk biyanget. Memang, beberapa kali kesini dan mencecap beragam rotinya, tetap yg terbaik roti pisangnya. Terkahir kesini roti pisangnya dibanderol 7K/bungkus. Oh ya, selaiknya toko pastry, di sini pun tersedia beragam roti lain seperti roti kacang, roti nanas, obijtkoek, roti gambang dsb dsb hingga panganan ringan. Pelayanan dari pegawainya ramah dan cekatan. Oh ya, roti di sini pun senantiasa fresh, lho. Lokasi berada sederetan dg ruko dekat Ramayan Mall.
review_translated_text: Legendary bakery in Malioboro. Having been around since colonial times, Toko Djoen is famous for its banana bread which is inuk biyanget. Indeed, I have been here several times and tried various breads, but the banana bread is still the best. Lastly, the banana bread is priced at 7K/pack. Oh yes, like a pastry shop, there are also various other breads available here such as peanut bread, pineapple bread, obijtkoek, gambang bread, etc., and even light snacks. The service from the employees is friendly and agile. Oh yes, the bread here is always fresh, you know. The location is in a row with shophouses near Ramayan Mall.

Suggestions for the cook, maybe dont use too much flavoring for the soup, maam, its better to use real chicken broth to make it delicious. review_text: Untuk tempat dengan konsep lawas, tempat ini cukup nyaman dan menenangkan. Terdapat pojok galeri yang menampilkan beberapa benda-benda jadul dan photo yang berisi silsilah raja-raja beberapa kerajaan, khususnya kerajaan di tengah pulau Jawa. Gerobak makanan dan minuman juga senada dengan konsep yang diusung. Sebagai catatan, hanya untuk dipertimbangkan, bukan untuk mendiskriminasi, pengelola tempat ini kristiani. Namun saya pun tetap merasa nyaman, atas keramahan pengelola.
review_translated_text: For a place with an old school concept, this place is quite comfortable and relaxing. There is a gallery corner which displays several old objects and photos containing the genealogy of the kings of several kingdoms, especially kingdoms in the middle of Java. Food and drink carts are also in line with the concept being promoted. For the record, just to be considerate, not to discriminate, the management of this place is Christian. However, I still felt comfortable, thanks to the friendliness of the manager.

review_text: Pecel nya enak,puli nya yummy  , apalagi yang goreng( beli yang belum digoreng juga ada) , jajanan tradisional pun banyak tersedia ,dari jadah jawut, jadah gemblong, woran, bandem celeng  ,klepon,tempe bacem, pokoknya kalau pas lewat Ponjong Gunungkidul jangan lupa kesini deh hehehe. The pecel is wrapped in teak leaves, Ms. Iken also applies good health protocols, wears a mask, and takes the food with her hands wrapped in plastic  , hopefully in the future her snacks will be more complete.

review_text: Tempatnya benar2 sejuk. Vibes hutan bambu dengan udara yang menyegarkan. Nyampe sana sekitar jam 8 pagi, masih sepi dan menjadi pengunjung pertama. Makanan prasmanan belum siap. Yang tersedia baru minuman dan beberapa jenis camilan ( tempe mendoan, bakwan, dll). Pelayanan cukup ramah. Waktu penyajian makanan yang dipesan juga cukup cepat. Teh pocinya kentel dan segar. Camilan bakwan + cocolan kecap pedas juga lumayan enak. Harga masih sangat terjangkau. Tersedia tempat parkir yang luas. Cocok untuk tempat ngadem dan menyegarkan pikiran dari hiruk pikuk kota.
review_translated_text: The place is really cool. Bamboo forest vibes with refreshing air. Arrived there around 8 in the morning, it was still quiet and I was the first visitor. Buffet food is not ready. Only drinks and several types of snacks are available (tempeh mendoan, bakwan, etc.). Service is quite friendly. The serving time for the food ordered is also quite fast. The teapot is thick and fresh. The bakwan snack + spicy soy sauce dip is also quite delicious. Prices are still very affordable. Ample parking is available. Suitable for a place to relax and refresh your mind from the hustle and bustle of the city.

review_translated_text: For the umpteenth time here, there have been several changes, previously there was a set buffet menu of Indonesian dishes (tends to be Javanese) such as Ndeso vegetables, mangut lele and others, but now the concept has changed to ala carte, order directly with menus such as pecel lele, fried rice, noodles and so on. etc. The taste is quite good, its just that I happened to get the fried vermicelli which was too salty. for traditional local authentic milk coffee. for the price, cheap and very affordable as a relaxing place, very nice, cool and naturally cool. there are several natural photo spots and an ATV arena for children and adults For toilets, maybe the floors can be controlled and cleaned more often The service is decent, only the male cashier is a bit rude. maybe even a cadet #jogjafoodstock #culinaryjogja #kulineryogya #jogjahits #kulinerjogjahits #kulinernusantara #yogyamakan #jogjamakan #makanjogja #makanyogya #culinaryreview #makandijogja #voilajogja #riderskulineran #jogjastreetfood #jogjafoodhunter #kulinerkekinian #snackskekinian #culinerlegendaris #makananviral #kojenkuliner #culinary #ngopidijogja #new culinary #current culinary

review_text: If you are looking to get good food and drinks, then I dont recommend this place at all.  We waited for the food for more than an hour. review_text: Sangat nyaman untuk duduk dan nugas. Spacious, sitting area-nya banyak, dengn jenis tempat dudik yang beragam. Saya pribadi suka nuansanya; charming, bangunan rumah lama yang struktur dan desainnya tidak dirombak besar-besaran, jadi nilai ke-dulu-annya masih terjaga. Kopinya pun enak dan well-made. Saya pesan Iced Americano Arabica (20k, sudah double shot). Dan oleh baristanya yang super ramah, saat itu diberi compliment gratis sekali refill, tapi alih-alih Iced Americano lagi, saya pilih Cappuccino, yang tak kalah enaknya. Chicken Quesadilla (27k) kombinasi perasan jeruk, potongan cabai rawit, tomat cincang, dan bawang merah-nya segar. Dalam satu porsi, terdiri dari 4 quesadilla. Sanger, atau kopi susu gula aren (21k), menurut saya terlalu manis, meskipun basisnya sudah double shot espresso. Parkir gratis.
review_translated_text: Very comfortable to sit and work on. Spacious, lots of sitting areas, with various types of seating. I personally like the feel; charming, old house whose structure and design have not been majorly overhauled, so its former value is still maintained. The coffee is delicious and well-made. I ordered Iced Americano Arabica (20k, double shot). And by the super friendly barista, at that time I was given a complimentary free refill, but instead of Iced Americano again, I chose Cappuccino, which was no less delicious. Chicken Quesadilla (27k) a combination of orange juice, chopped cayenne pepper, chopped tomatoes and fresh red onions. In one serving, it consists of 4 quesadillas. Sanger, or palm sugar milk coffee (21k), in my opinion is too sweet, even though the base is a double shot of espresso. Free parking.

review_text: Beberapa kali ke sini untuk nugas, dan ya, ketagihan. Suasananya tenang dan kondusif untuk nugas, makanan dan minuman enak semua. Dari segi fasilitas sangat lengkap ya, wifi kencang, mushola bersih (ada mukena dan wangi). Kamar mandi bersih, tidak bau tapi juga tidak wangi (kalau diberi pengharum kamar mandi mungkin lebih oke). Hehe My fav drink here will be herbanera, mungkin semacam kopsus gula aren with a hint of ginger and spice. Love the combination. Main coursenya sejauh ini ga ada yang fail dan super worth the price, masaknya niat. The mushroom sauce is good, sauted vegetable di ricebowlnya juga enak. Quesadillanya juga enak, saucenya segeeer banget. Staffs are very friendly and helpful. Alat makan ga sengaja jatuh langsung diganti, dibantu ngeluarin motor juga ketika parkir penuh. Parkir gratis, tapi mungkin agak sempit kalau bawa mobil. Lange will be my fav kofisyop di bilangan Pakuningratan. Thumbs up
review_translated_text: Been here several times for assignments, and yes, addicted. The atmosphere is calm and conducive to work, the food and drinks are all delicious. In terms of facilities, it is very complete, fast wifi, clean prayer room (there are mukenas and it smells good). The bathroom is clean, not smelly but also not fragrant (if you had bathroom freshener it might be better). Haha My fav drink here will be herbanera, maybe a kind of palm sugar kopsus with a hint of ginger and spice. Love the combination. There are no failures in the main course so far and its super worth the price, its delicious. The mushroom sauce is good, the sauted vegetables in the rice bowl are also delicious. The quesadilla is also delicious, the sauce is really fresh. Staffs are very friendly and helpful. The cutlery that accidentally fell was immediately replaced, helped to remove the motorbike when the parking lot was full. Parking is free, but it might be a bit tight if you bring a car. Lange will be my favorite kofisyop in the Pakuningratan area. Thumbs up

Terus pesen vegetarian salad, enak juga sesuai ekspektasiku Untuk pelayanan disini ramah buangett mas mas e grapyak pol dan sabar menghadapi berbagai macam karakter customernya. Untuk penyajian makanan dan minumannya terhitung cepat, ga sampe 15 menit makanan dan minuman udah dateng. Untuk tempatnya ada indoor ac, outdoor semi teras gitu, sama outdoor yg di dalem cafenya jadi ga keliatan org kalo lg nongkrong wkwk. Yang indoor ac tentunya non smooking yaa. Selain itu di outdoor yg di dalem cafe, ada semi indoornya gitu yg bisa dipakai buat kerja kelompok asik! Colokan jelas buanyak disini, gausah ragu. Wifi kenceng, musik yg di play juga seru-seru. Cukup menemani cengkrama malam ini bersama kawan-kawanku. Harganya cukup affordable juga. Yang masih terjangkau buat mahasiswa mendang mending kaya saya. Overall aku sangat suka, next time kalo bingung mau nongkrong kemana, kayanya ini bisa jadi pilihan.

review_translated_text: Came here tonight because my friend invited me. It just opened last Saturday. Its a really friendly place, good for hanging out, doing work or just chatting. The menu is like a normal coffee shop, I thought the matcha order was really delicious, because it still had a hint of bitterness. Then order the vegetarian salad, its also delicious according to my expectations The service here is friendly, bro, bro and grapyak pol and patient with the various characters of the customers. Serving food and drinks is relatively fast, in less than 15 minutes the food and drinks arrived. As for the place, there is indoor air conditioning, an outdoor semi-terrace like that, and an outdoor area inside the cafe so people dont see it if youre hanging out. The indoor AC is of course non-smoking. Apart from that, in the outdoor area inside the cafe, there is a semi indoor area that can be used for fun group work! There are obviously a lot of plugs here, dont worry. The wifi is fast, the music being played is also fun. Just accompany me to chat tonight with my friends. The price is quite affordable too. What is still affordable for students is better like me. Overall I really like it, next time if Im confused about where to hang out, I think this could be an option.

review_text: Tempat nya mudah di temukan karena srategis dekat dengan tugu jogja, depan persis hotel Grand Zuri dan berada di dalam toko dagadu. Terdapat 3 lantai, Untuk pemesanan di lantai 1 bersebelahan dengan store dagadu persis tanpa penyekat. Untuk lantai 2 area indoor ber AC dan lantai 3 outdoor.Untuk kafe yang berada di dalam dagadu cukup work tray lah... Untuk harga ya standar kafe pada umumnya mulai dari 20k an untuk makanan 30k an untuk minuman. But taste of food biasa saja, bahkan saya pesan salad,  maaf untuk sayuran kubisnya banyak bercak hitamnya  dan sedikit untuk harga yang lumayan mahal untuk salad. But overall masih bisa di nikmati semua makanan yang saya pesan. Untuk suasanya di area indoor cukup baik lah, AC terasa dan lumayan lega karena cukup banyak kursi. Namun WC area indoor perlu di tingkatkan lagi untuk kebersihan juga karena waktu saya kesana pintu WC sedikit rusak dan harus minta tolong kepada security dagadu. Untuk area outdoor belum coba karena waktu kesana sedang perbaikan.
review_translated_text: The place is easy to find because it is strategically close to the Jogja monument, right in front of the Grand Zuri hotel and inside the Dagadu shop. There are 3 floors. For orders on the 1st floor next to the Dagadu store, there are no partitions. For the 2nd floor, the indoor area is air-conditioned and the 3rd floor is outdoor. For the cafe inside Dagadu, just a work tray... As for prices, cafe standards generally start from 20k for food to 30k for drinks. But the taste of food is normal, I even ordered a salad, sorry for the cabbage, it had a lot of black spots and a little bit for the price which is quite expensive for a salad. But overall I can still enjoy all the food I ordered. The atmosphere in the indoor area is quite good, the air conditioning feels good and its quite spacious because there are quite a lot of chairs. However, the indoor toilet area needs to be improved for cleanliness because when I went there the toilet door was a little damaged and I had to ask Dagadu security for help. Havent tried the outdoor area yet because it was under construction when we went there.

Tempatnya nyaman dan asik utk menikmati senja dari rooftop, dan nyaman juga utk nugas di lantai 2 dgn smoking area juga. Harga menu ramah dikantong, pelayanan cepet, rasa makanan & minuman enak dan porsi nya pas. Nyobain pesen iced coffie aren rasanya pas bgt di lidah dgn harga 28rb nett. Hihi cukup murah menurutku Overall first time ke sini aku cocok krn tempatnya nyaman dan harga pas dikantong. Bakal jadi list coffee shop favorit ku sih ini. Makasih lokio cafe. Bakal balik lagi ke sini
review_translated_text: Try coming here because you often pass by Jln Mangkubumi. I really liked the service, the first time you entered you were immediately greeted by the friendly cashier ladies. The place is comfortable and cool to enjoy the sunset from the rooftop, and also comfortable for working on the 2nd floor with a smoking area too. The menu prices are pocket friendly, the service is fast, the food & drinks taste delicious and the portions are just right. Try ordering iced coffee and it tastes really good on your tongue at a price of 28 thousand nett. Hihi, quite cheap in my opinion Overall, the first time I came here, it suited me because the place was comfortable and the price was right in my pocket. This will be on my list of favorite coffee shops. Thanks chive cafe. Will come back here again

review_text: Relax, enjoy the coffe, gelato, food &snack n buy the original tshirt DAGADU Djokja.

(+) - lokasi strategis dari wisatawan - one stop shopping, belanja oleh-oleh sekalian nongkrong utk menikmati gelato atau kopi - menunya variatif, coffee & non coffee lengkap, ada snack & makanan berat juga - tempatnya cukup nyaman (kemarin saya di lt. 2), ada smoking area di balkonnya, kece juga - rekomen kopi pistachionya, rasanya unik!! 5/5 (-) - brulee bomb yg saya pesen, dalamnya masih dingin   kemungkinan menggoreng dgn api terlalu besar/saat minyak belum begitu panas tapi makanan sudah dimasukkan ke penggorengan - alat makan utk snacknya menggunakan sendok kecil, sepertinya lebih cocok dgn garpu kecil - pelayanannya 50:50. Cukup jelas menerangkan ttg menu, tapi mungkin kemarin waktu saya kesana seperti terburu2 dalam melayani, jd kurang perhatian ke customer
review_translated_text: (+) - strategic location from tourists - one stop shopping, shopping for souvenirs while hanging out to enjoy gelato or coffee - The menu is varied, complete with coffee & non-coffee, there are snacks & heavy meals too - the place is quite comfortable (yesterday I was on the 2nd floor), there is a smoking area on the balcony, cool too - recommend the pistachio coffee, it tastes unique!! 5/5 (-) - the brulee bomb that I ordered, the inside is still cold   possibly frying with too high heat/when the oil is not yet hot but the food has been put into the frying pan - Cutlery for snacks uses a small spoon, it seems more suitable with a small fork - service is 50:50. It explains the menu clearly enough, but maybe yesterday when I went there I seemed to be in a rush to serve, so I didnt pay attention to customers
