review_text: Berada di titik strategis kota Yogyakarta, dekat banget sama Tugu Yogya. Mampir disini bisa sekalian jalan jalan menikmati ambience Tugu Yogya dan sekitarnya. Kedai Kolega disini menunya sama dengan Kedai Kolega di Gedongkuning. Konsepnya juga hampir sama, ada store Dagadu nya, kafe, tempat nongkrong. Cuman memang lebih sempit daripada di Gedongkuning. Parkir mobil akan kesulitan. Mending kendaraan roda dua atau pakai kendaraan online saja. Instagramable juga. Banyak spot keren yang dihiasi dengan mural juga colorful. Jam bukanya asik banget, jam 7 pagi udah buka. Jadi mau cari sarapan bisa banget. Nongkrong pagi  juga asik, karena masih sepi.  Ruangan ber AC nya akan lebih banyak daripada outdoor (smoking area). Ada ruang meeting imut juga bisa untuk 8 orang saja deh. Terdiri dari 2 lantai. Lantai bawah agak lebih sempit, include Kitchen. Lantai dua lebih leluasa dan ada buku buku bacaan yang bisa dibaca ditempat. Stafnya ramah. Wifi oke, AC juga dingin banget. Stop kontak juga mudah di beberapa colokan listrik tempat duduk, selebihnya tidak dekat dengan colokan listrik. Karena kesana pas masih finishing renovasi, maka masih ada beberapa tukang yang bekerja wira wiri, bahkan sofa sofa masih dicover plastik (karena baru).
review_translated_text: Located at a strategic point in the city of Yogyakarta, very close to the Yogya Monument. Stopping here can also take a walk and enjoy the ambience of Tugu Yogya and its surroundings. Kedai Kolega here has the same menu as Kedai Kolega in Gedongkuning. The concept is almost the same, there is a Dagadu store, cafe, place to hang out. Its just narrower than in Gedongkuning. Car parking will be difficult. Its better to use a two-wheeled vehicle or just use an online vehicle. Instagrammable too. Many cool spots are decorated with colorful murals. The opening hours are really cool, it opens at 7 am. So if you want to find breakfast, you can really do it. Hanging out in the morning  is also cool, because its still quiet. There will be more air-conditioned rooms than outdoor (smoking areas). There is also a cute meeting room for just 8 people. Consists of 2 floors. The lower floor is a bit narrower, including the kitchen. The second floor is more spacious and there are books that can be read on the spot. The staff are friendly. Wifi is okay, AC is also very cold. The sockets are also easy to find in some of the seat power sockets, the rest are not close to the power sockets. Because we were there when we were still finishing renovations, there were still several craftsmen working independently, even the sofas were still covered in plastic (because they were new).

review_text: Nice working spot in Jogja

The newest branch of Peacock Coffee in Jogja. Selain di cabang Semarang & Palagan, skrg ada di Monginsidi Guest House. Tempatnya ngga terlalu luas krn gabung sm guest house ya. Ada indoor ac, smoking room dan outdoor. Yang di dlm lbh utk komunal usage sedangkan luar lbh banyak opsi tempat duduknya. Overall lumayan soal layout nya. Menu2nya banyak, minuman kopinya still bring back the old memories years ago waktu mereka msh di Mustokoweni. Hazelnut latte nya masih memorable bgt rasanya plus the legendary mug that I had still same like the old days. Love it But the (-) is lack of food options. Cm ada snacks itu pun ngga lengkap yah.    Pdhl klo kesana tuh pengennya bs sekalian makan siang gitu loh. Cm nggak ada makanan beratnya, sayang bgt. Moga next time bisa lah ditambah opsi makanan berat. Apalagi mereka buka 24 jam ya lebih baik bs sediakan makanan berat. The other (-) is toilet nya juga gabung di dlm guest house, too narrow pula.   Jd agak repot yah klo mau ke toilet, nggak ada tissue juga. Smg next time lbh OK.
review_translated_text: The newest branch of Peacock Coffee in Jogja. Apart from the Semarang & Palagan branches, it is now available at Monginsidi Guest House. The place isnt too big because its combined with a guest house. There is indoor air conditioning, smoking room and outdoor. The inside is more for communal use while the outside has more seating options. Overall its not bad regarding the layout. The menu is extensive, the coffee drinks still bring back the old memories years ago when they were still in Mustokoweni. The hazelnut latte is still very memorable, plus the legendary mug that I had is still the same as the old days. Love it But the (-) is lack of food options. Even if there are snacks, theyre not complete.    Even if you go there, you want to be able to have lunch at the same time, you know. Theres no heavy food, thats a shame. Hopefully next time we can add heavy meal options. Moreover, they are open 24 hours so its better to be able to provide heavy food. The other (-) is that the toilet is also included in the guest house, too narrow too.   So its a bit of a hassle when you want to go to the toilet, theres no tissue either. Hopefully next time it will be OK.

review_text: Dapat info tempat ini dari Maps,  lihat review yang banyak bintang 4 dan 5. Setelah didatangi,  KECEWA.  Tempatnya seperti gak terurus,  kamar mandi lantainya licin sekali,  hati hati jika bawa anak kecil. Yang bilang tempat ini sejuk,  saya yakin mereka sering kena panas. Hahaha. Makanannya sih enak, tapi cara mengolahnya bikin ikan goreng yang seharusnya bisa dinikmati dagingnya,  menjadi tinggal sedikit sekali. Dan harganya MAHAL menurut saya yang orang kota. Tempat terpencil meski bisa ditemukan via Maps. Nurutin anak ingin mancing, sewa stik pancing harga 5.000 tapi gak ada umpannya. Dua jam lebih gak dapat ikan. Kelihatan ada ikannya saja tidak. Satu lagi,  jika pesan makan ditempat ini,  harga tidak sesuai menu. Nanti untuk sambal dan lalapan akan di charge lagi,  dan itu bukan termasuk yang ada di daftar menu.  Sedang daftar menunya hanya berupa menu ikan gurami,  nila,  bawal, yang  bisa goreng,  bakar,  bakar madu, asam manis. Juga nasi putih,  teh manis. Yang tidak tertera disana dan disajikan, anda harus bayar lagi. Aneh, biasanya kalau ke resto ikan bakar atau goreng,  yang namanya sambal atau lalapan yang sedikit saja tidak kena charge lagi. Mengecewakan.
review_translated_text: Got information about this place from Maps, looked at the reviews which had lots of 4 and 5 stars. After visiting, I was DISAPPOINTED. The place looks neglected, the bathroom floor is very slippery, be careful if you bring small children. Those who say this place is cool, Im sure they often get hot. Ha ha ha. The food is delicious, but the way it is prepared means that the fried fish, which should be able to be enjoyed for meat, becomes very small. And the price is EXPENSIVE in my opinion for city people. Remote place although it can be found via Maps. According to the child, he wanted to fish, rented a fishing pole for 5,000 but there was no bait. I didnt catch any fish for more than two hours. It doesnt look like there are any fish. One more thing, if you order food at this place, the price does not match the menu. Later, the chili sauce and fresh vegetables will be charged again, and that is not included in the menu list. Meanwhile, the menu list only includes gourami, tilapia, pomfret fish, which can be fried, grilled, grilled with honey, sweet and sour. Also white rice, sweet tea. If it is not listed there and served, you have to pay again. Its strange, usually when you go to a grilled or fried fish restaurant, even a small amount of chili sauce or fresh vegetables is no longer charged. Disappointing.

review_text: TLDR ; Good for chat, a relaxing place to hangout with friends. Review De Cored Coffee & Eatery Tempat 4/5 Bertempat di Barat Tugu Jogja, De Cored mudah di akses. Tempat parkir cukup sempit, jika menggunakan mobil bisa parkir di bahu jalan. Ruangan tempat duduk semi-outdoor, suasana tempatnya lebih mengarah ke santai, enak untuk mengobrol dengan teman. Saya rekomendasikan tempat duduk dekat barista jika ingin bekerja karena meja disitu pas untuk laptop, namun yang disayangkan adalah stop kontak listrik yang hanya ada satu untuk setiap meja, jadi harus pinjam terminal atau bawa sendiri. Kopi 4/5 Harga kopi di 20-30k, harga yang standar untuk kafe di pusat kota. Saya pesan Sea Salt Coffee dengan harga 26k, rasa sesuai ekspektasi. Sea Salt Caramelnya terasa, tanpa mengalahkan rasa dari Espresso. Namun menurut saya lebih cocok untuk menunggu hingga es sedikit meleleh karena terlalu manis jika langsung diminum. Pelayanan 5/5 Barista dan Pegawai ramah dan baik dalam melayani. Kalau boleh nambah, bisa pakai pakaian yang lebih tertutup karena Koyonya kelihatan wkwk. Kamar Mandi 4/5 Ada dua kamar mandi sedang, tidak kotor walaupun lampunya remang-remang. Tapi banyak lalat limbah yang nongkrong disitu jadi lebih baik kalau dibersihkan.
review_translated_text: TLDR ; Good for chat, a relaxing place to hang out with friends. De Cored Coffee & Eatery Review Place 4/5 Located west of Tugu Jogja, De Cored is easy to access. Parking space is quite narrow, if you use a car you can park on the side of the road. Semi-outdoor seating, the atmosphere is more relaxed, nice for chatting with friends. I recommend a seat near the barista if you want to work because the table there is suitable for a laptop, but the unfortunate thing is that there is only one electrical socket for each table, so you have to borrow a terminal or bring your own. Coffee 4/5 Coffee prices are around 20-30k, a standard price for a cafe in the city center. I ordered Sea Salt Coffee for 26k, the taste met expectations. The Sea Salt Caramel is delicious, without overpowering the taste of the Espresso. However, in my opinion it is more suitable to wait until the ice melts a little because it is too sweet to drink straight away. Service 5/5 Baristas and employees are friendly and good at serving. If you can add more, you can wear more closed clothes because the patch looks haha. Bathroom 4/5 There are two medium bathrooms, not dirty even though the lights are dim. But there are lots of waste flies that hang out there so it would be better if they were cleaned.

Dukungan free WiFi saat ngopi atau menikmati makanan, membuat tempat ini semakin layak Anda kunjungi.

A fairly diverse selection of food and drink menus is the advantage of this poci stall. This stalls mainstay menu is fried chicken and Vietnamese coffee. Free WiFi support when drinking coffee or enjoying food makes this place even more worth visiting.

review_text: I recently visited this Korean street food restaurant and I have to say, it was absolutely amazing. From start to finish, the experience was fantastic. The staff were incredibly friendly and welcoming, and the atmosphere was vibrant and exciting. Now, on to the food. The menu had a great selection of classic Korean street food dishes, as well as some more unique options that I hadnt seen before. Everything we ordered was delicious - the flavors were bold and authentic, and the portions were generous. Some of my personal favorites were the Korean fried chicken, the kimbap ,and the ramyeon noodle. In addition to the food, the drinks menu was impressive as well. They had a good selection of Korean beverages,one my favorite is oksusu (corn starch tea) Overall, I highly recommend this Korean street food restaurant. Its a great spot for a casual meal with friends or a fun night out, and the food and atmosphere are top-notch. 5 stars all around!

review_text: Kalau kamu suka suasana sepi di tengah keriuhan pusat kota; cafe ini pilihan terbaik. Kami tidak sengaja menemukannya. Kamu bisa duduk dengan segelas kopi, beberapa halaman buku, atau layar laptop. Bagus juga kalau mau sekadar melamun. Kopi susu karamelnya enak, harga murah. Kedai kopi kecil ini tidak banyak aksesoris; tempelan-tempelan hiasan di setiap ruang. Semuanya sederhana saja. Sebuah bekas rumah tua yang disulap jadi kedai dengan kursi kursi yang pas, meja yang nyaman; semua memanggilmu untuk duduk beberapa waktu disini, dengan segelas kopi dan melihat hidup ya cuma gini gini.
review_translated_text: If you like a quiet atmosphere amidst the hustle and bustle of the city center; This cafe is the best choice. We stumbled upon it by accident. You can sit with a cup of coffee, a few pages of a book, or a laptop screen. Its also good if you want to just daydream. The caramel milk coffee is delicious, the price is cheap. This small coffee shop doesnt have many accessories; decorative hangings in every room. Its all simple. A former old house transformed into a shop with suitable chairs, comfortable tables; everyone is calling you to sit here for a while, with a cup of coffee and see life just like this.

review_text: Sebuah kafe rumahan yang nyaman sekali untuk berlama-lama di dalamnya. Lokasinya hanya sepelemparan batu dari Alun-Alun Selatan. Mungkin karena kafe baru, pelanggannya masih belum terlalu banyak. Pelayanannya luar biasa ramah. Saat datang pada sore hari sekitar jam 16.00, seorang pelayan yang sepertinya juga pemilik kafe menyambut dengan ceria dan bilang bahwa mereka baru saja buka hari Minggu itu karena ada acara keluarga sebelumnya. Waktu bertanya sudah berapa lama kafe ini berdiri, mbak yang melayani menjawab, Baru tiga bulan. Saya memesan choco latte, platter, dan roti bakar choco cheese. Rasa ketiga menu itu enak dan pas. Harganya pun pas di kantong dengan porsi yang lumayan mengenyangkan. Bahkan roti bakarnya tidak habis, padahal enak banget. Saya akan kembali lagi ke sini. Mungkin beberapa kali seminggu. Saya bahkan berkelakar dengan teman saya, Wah bisa nih jadi rumah kedua! Tempat yang cocok sekali untuk bekerja sambil laptopan atau hanya nongkrong/ngobrol bareng teman atau keluarga!
review_translated_text: A homely cafe that is very comfortable to linger in. The location is just a stones throw from South Square. Maybe because the cafe is new, there arent many customers yet. The service is extraordinarily friendly. When we arrived in the afternoon at around 16.00, a waiter who seemed to be the owner of the cafe greeted us cheerfully and said that they had just opened that Sunday because there was a family event beforehand. When asked how long this cafe had been around, the lady serving answered, Only three months. I ordered a choco latte, platter and choco cheese toast. The taste of the three menus was delicious and just right. The price is right on the pocket with portions that are quite filling. Even the toast wasnt finished, even though it was really delicious. I will come back here again. Maybe a few times a week. I even joked with my friend, Wow, this could be a second home! A perfect place to work on your laptop or just hang out/chat with friends or family!

Lokasi: lokasinya sendiri sedikit masuk-masuk dari jalan utama, jalanan cor blok, licin disaat musim penghujan seperti ini, ditambah berlumut, bisa dilalui kendaraan roda duaaupun toda empat, yg terpenting tetap hati-hati saat berkendara Tempat: sejuk, asri, nyaman, menyatu dengan alam karena berada di alam terbuka, disuguhkan dengan pemandangan alam yg sangat indah baik pagi siang ataupun malam, terjaga kebersihannya & jauh dari hiruk pikuk perkotaan, cocok untuk bersantai bersama pasangan, bahkan rombongan, karena berada di atas ketinggian & bisa menikmati hampatan perbukitan & bentangan sungai progo Fasilitas: dari segi fasilitas sendiri sangat lengkap, mulai dari: -Toilet, untuk toiletnya sendiri cukup memadahi, serta terjaga kebersihannya, -Tempat ibadah/masjid  yang cukup luas & besar yg berada di bagian bawah -Parkiran yang cukup luas & memadahi baik roda dua maupun roda empat Makanan & Minuman: -Varian: cukup banyak -Rasa: untuk rasa ya relatif, tapi menurut saya cukup enak lah -Harga: menurut saya masih terjangkau banget & bisa dibilang cukup murah Pelayanan: cukup memuaskan Sebenernya biasa saja sih, beberapa spot/roof top terlihat kurang terawat & beberapa bangunan terlihat mangkrak pembangunannya, tempat ngopinya juga biasa
review_translated_text: Location: the location itself is a little in and out of the main road, cast block road, slippery during the rainy season like this, plus mossy, can be passed by two-wheeled vehicles or four-wheeled vehicles, the most important thing is to be careful when driving Place: cool, beautiful, comfortable, at one with nature because it is in the open air, presented with very beautiful natural views both morning, afternoon and evening, kept clean & far from the hustle and bustle of urban areas, suitable for relaxing with a partner, even a group, because is at a height & can enjoy the expanse of hills & stretches of the Progo river Facilities: in terms of the facilities themselves, they are very complete, starting from: -Toilet, the toilet itself is adequate and kept clean, -The place of worship/mosque is quite spacious & large at the bottom -Parking is quite spacious & accommodates both two-wheeled and four-wheeled vehicles Food & Drink: -Variations: quite a lot -Taste: taste is relative, but I think its quite delicious -Price: in my opinion it is still very affordable & could be said to be quite cheap Service: quite satisfactory Actually, its just normal, some spots/roof tops look poorly maintained & some buildings look like their construction is stalled, the coffee place is also ordinary

review_text: 30 Agustus 23/ Nasi kucing 5rb, tempe 1rb an, teh hangat 3rb. Nasi kucingnya agak mahal, tapi emang porsinya gede 1 mangkok nasi. Nasinya juga fresh dari magic com, diporsiin terus ditaruh di piringnya dan dikasih sambel teri. Selain sambel teri juga ada pilihan oseng oseng ati. Sambel terinya cukup enak, pedes gurih dengan teri yang nggak mengecewakan. Tempenya tipis, jadi 1rb itungannya agak mahal tapi ya sudahlah. Namanya juga harga angkringan di pusat wisata. Teh angetnya oke, standar. Tempatnya pas setelah gapura pertama alun alun dari arah 0km. Duduknya bisa di dalem lesehan agak luas, untuk di luar juga ada 1 meja kursi panjang gitu. Juga bisa di bangku trotoar 0km. Lumayan syahdu sih suasananya, berangkringan ria di 0km. Nggak ada wastafel, nggak ada tisu. Bayar harus tunai. Overall pretty good, a bit pricey tapi dapat dipahami untuk tempat wisata. Hitungannya masih lebih murah dari sebelah sebelahnya anyway. Bisa lah mampir kalau mau sok syahdu atau ngganjel perut dulu.
review_translated_text: 30 August 23/ Rice cat 5 thousand, tempeh 1 thousand, hot tea 3 thousand. The cat rice is a bit expensive, but the portion is really big, 1 bowl of rice. The rice is also fresh from magic com, portioned and placed on a plate and topped with anchovy sauce. Apart from anchovy chili sauce, there is also the option of stir-fried liver. The anchovy sauce is quite delicious, spicy and tasty with anchovies that dont disappoint. The tempeh is thin, so 1 thousand is a bit expensive but thats okay. It is also called the price of angkringan at the tourist center. The hot tea is okay, standard. The place is right after the first gate of the alun-alun from the direction 0km. You can sit inside the rather spacious lesehan, outside there is also 1 long table and chairs. Also available on the 0km sidewalk bench. The atmosphere is quite serene, having fun hanging out at 0km. There is no sink, no tissue. Payment must be in cash. Overall pretty good, a bit pricey but understandable for a tourist spot. The calculation is still cheaper than the next door anyway. You can stop by if you want to act cool or have an upset stomach first.

review_text: Pas aku kesana cuacanya bagus banget bisa nyore  sekalian liat sunset di temenin kopi hitam  . Kalo balik ke Jogja lagi bakal sering dateng kesini makanannya enak2 semua. Angkringan tapi unik model prasmanan sambel teri dan oseng tempe nya.
review_translated_text: When I went there the weather was really nice, I could relax and watch the sunset accompanied by black coffee  . If I return to Jogja again, I will often come here, the food is all delicious. Angkringan but unique with a buffet style of anchovy chili sauce and stir-fried tempe.

review_text: BeQuan Mba Ratna adalah tujuan wajib bagi pencinta makanan praktis berkualitas. Lokasinya yang strategis membuatnya mudah di temukan. Kualitas premium produk frozen food mereka benar-benar memukau. Rasanya lezat dan khas, serta harganya yang terjangkau membuatnya menjadi pilihan utama dalam belanja makanan beku. Jadi pilihan utama kalau pas lebaran, karena banyak toko lain yang tutup hihi
review_translated_text: BeQuan Mba Ratna is a mandatory destination for lovers of quality practical food. Its strategic location makes it easy to find. The premium quality of their frozen food products is truly stunning. The taste is delicious and distinctive, and the affordable price makes it the main choice when shopping for frozen food. So the main choice during Eid, because many other shops are closed hihi

review_text: BeQuan Mba Ratna benar-benar memahami kebutuhan pelanggan. Lokasi toko yang nyaman dan mudah di temukan membuat belanja jadi lebih praktis. Menawarkan produk frozen food dengan kualitas yang enak dan rasanya seperti masakan rumahan. Terlebih lagi, harga-harganya sangat bersahabat bagi semua kalangan, terutama bagi saya mahasiswa yang iseng camping di sermo menyempatkan mampir untuk belanja sosis bernardi untuk bahan makanan saat camping.
review_translated_text: BeQuan Mba Ratna really understands customer needs. The stores location is convenient and easy to find, making shopping more practical. Offers frozen food products with delicious quality and tastes like home cooking. Whats more, the prices are very friendly for all groups, especially for me, a student who was just camping in Sermo and stopped by to shop for Bernardi sausages for food while camping.

review_text: Lokasi toko frozen food BeQuan Mba Ratna sangat strategis, mudah di akses dari Pusat kota wates. Kualitas makanan beku yang mereka tawarkan sungguh premium, tidak ada kompromi dalam rasa dan tekstur. Namun, yang membuat saya lebih suka adalah harga yang tetap ramah di kantong. Menemukan toko dengan kualitas sebaik ini dan harga terjangkau adalah suatu hiden gem buat anak muda.
review_translated_text: The location of the BeQuan Mba Ratna frozen food shop is very strategic, easy to access from Wates city center. The quality of the frozen food they offer is truly premium, there is no compromise in taste and texture. However, what makes me prefer it is the price which is still pocket friendly. Finding a shop with this good quality and affordable prices is a hidden gem for young people.

review_text: Pengalaman belanja di toko frozen food BeQuan sangat menyenangkan. Produknya tersedia dengan lengkap dan kemasan yang rapi. Saya telah mencoba beberapa jenis makanan dan semuanya lezat. Harga yang terjangkau membuatnya menjadi pilihan terbaik untuk kebutuhan acara di rumah.
review_translated_text: The shopping experience at the BeQuan frozen food store is very pleasant. The products are available complete and neatly packaged. I have tried several types of food and they are all delicious. The affordable price makes it the best choice for home event needs.

review_text: Saya sangat senang dengan produk frozen food dari BeQuan. Kualitasnya terjaga dengan baik, rasa dan teksturnya tetap enak seperti makanan segar. Pilihan variasi menu yang mereka tawarkan juga cukup beragam, cocok untuk memenuhi kebutuhan keluarga.
review_translated_text: I am very happy with frozen food products from BeQuan. The quality is well maintained, the taste and texture remain delicious like fresh food. The choice of menu variations they offer is also quite diverse, suitable to meet family needs.

Awalnya mau pesen minum sama makan, dan pesenlah tu nasi goreng kalau ga salah. Tapi katanya kosong, yaudahlah pesen aja kentang goreng. Gak lama kan yaudah setelah pesen naiklah ke atas, dan di atas tu bener2 kotor banget banyak sampah kulit kacang, Putung rokok sama gelas2 kotor belum di bersihin dan OMG kotor banget huhu sampe aku dan temenku ngebatin apa ga dibersihin dulu sebelum buka:(. Singkat cerita selang agak lama baru dibersihin tu gelas kotor yg banyak bgt gitu kan ya, terus pesennya es Milo kalau ga salah, kalau ga Milo anget tapi datengnya tu milonya GK manis sama sekali dan encer banget     dah gakmau berkata2 apalagi yaudah deh pindah tempat aja. Tapi sebetulnya view dari atas tu bagus buat ngeliat bawah, tapi pelayananny aj yg kurang. Sekian review dr aku.
review_translated_text: Honest review from me, guys, once I was here on a Sunday around 1 in the afternoon and it happened to be open, so I just ordered, but from the start I didnt have a good feeling. Why? Because when I was watching, I remember there were 2 guys, or 3, I forget, and there was just a guitar there. Yes, I thought people were hanging out like that, right, but it turns out he was the one selling it. Initially I wanted to order a drink and a meal, and I ordered fried rice if Im not mistaken. But he said it was empty, so just order fries. Not long after ordering, I went upstairs, and the top was really dirty, lots of peanut shell rubbish, cigarette butts and dirty glasses hadnt been cleaned yet and OMG it was so dirty that my friend and I wondered if we should not clean it first before opening it :(. Short. The story goes that after a while before I cleaned it, there were a lot of dirty glasses, right? Then I ordered iced Milo, if Im not mistaken, if not, Milo was hot, but when it arrived, the Milo wasnt sweet at all and was really runny     I didnt want to say anything, let alone move on. Thats all. But actually the view from the top is good for looking down, but the service is lacking. Thats my review.

review_text: Eyang Tun has the best and most delicious Songgo Buwono   and it became my favorite!

Eyang Tun berhasil mengajak lidahku merasakan cita rasa yang berbeda, unik, dan otentik. Pastel, risoles adalah jajanan pasar yang dijual disetiap sudut Jogja dan bukan rahasia umum lagi, rasanya sering bikin trauma. Tapi Eyang Tun (lagi lagi) berhasil membuat lidahku takjub. Kulit pastel: renyah, gurih, terasa pake susu dan keju (padahal tidak pakai) dan ketebalan kulitnya pas. Isinya: telur bacem (khas Jogja), daging sapi, wortel, dan kaya rempah. Kalo gini, aku jadi tau kalo tekstur dan cita rasa antara  Pastel dan Jalangkote (jajanan khas Makasar) itu beda! Risoles ragout ayam juga juara!. Ketebalan kulit pas, ga terlalu tebal dan terasa gurih (ga hambar). Isi ragout ayamnya manis dan gurih. Ini jajanan yg aku ga temuin dimana-mana, yi Songgo Buwono. Wah cerdas sih, tekstur Susnya kering, ladanya terasa, gurih banget. Mayones asem yg dibuat sendiri bener-bener memperkaya rasa. Oo satu lagi. Aku makan ayam afrika panggang. Wah rasanya bener2 baru bagi lidahku. Unik, adalah kata yg tepat utk menggambarkan rasanya. Makanan ini membuktikan kalau pangan dan cita rasa itu ga terbatas ruang. Aku benar-benar merasakan, setiap elemen panganan ini punya rasanya sendiri, dan ketika disatukan saling berpadu. Pas! Eyang Tun, terima kasih ya sudah memberi kesempatan lidahku merasakan cita rasa panganan elit zaman kolonial di Jogja!
review_translated_text: Eyang Tun succeeded in inviting my tongue to taste different, unique and authentic flavors. Pastels and rissoles are market snacks sold in every corner of Jogja and its no secret that their taste often causes trauma. But Eyang Tun (again) managed to amaze my tongue. Pastel skin: crunchy, tasty, tastes like it uses milk and cheese (even though it doesnt) and the thickness of the skin is just right. It contains: bacem eggs (typical of Jogja), beef, carrots and rich spices. In this way, I know that the texture and taste between Pastel and Jalangkote (a typical Makasar snack) are different! The chicken ragout rissoles are also a winner! The thickness of the skin is just right, not too thick and tastes delicious (not bland). The chicken ragout filling is sweet and savory. This is a snack that I cant find anywhere, yi Songgo Buwono. Wow, thats clever, the texture of the milk is dry, the pepper is delicious, its really tasty. Homemade tamarind mayonnaise really enriches the taste. Oh, one more thing. I ate grilled African chicken. Wow, this taste is really new to my tongue. Unique, is the right word to describe the taste. This food proves that food and taste are not limited by space. I really feel that each element of this food has its own taste, and when put together they complement each other. Fit! Eyang Tun, thank you for giving my tongue the opportunity to taste the taste of colonial era elite food in Jogja!

review_text: Eyang Tun ini spesialis jajanan dan masakan Indonesia yag terinfluens Eropa. Barusan COD pesenan berupa pastel, risoles dan songgo buwono. Enak banget, pastelnya walau isi daging gak kering--moist banget. Ragout sapi dalem risolesnya juara. Songgo buwononya juga enak banget, dengan mayones mustard homemade yang manis asem. Aku belum nemu lagi yang jual jajan songgo buwono. Pokoknya recommended banget sih, will def order more next time.
review_translated_text: Eyang Tun is a specialist in Indonesian snacks and dishes with European influences. Just ordered COD in the form of pastels, risoles and songgo buwono. Its really delicious, even though the pastel is filled with meat, its not dry - its really moist. The beef ragout in the risoles is a winner. The songgo buwono is also really delicious, with sweet and sour homemade mustard mayonnaise. I havent found anyone selling songgo buwono snacks yet. Anyway, really recommended, will definitely order more next time.
